episodes.plot: Raylan helps Wendy track down Kendal Crowe after he disappears with an "uncle," while Boyd and the rest of the Crowe family try to get their drugs and dead bodies back across the Mexican border.

episodes.title: Wrong Roads
episodes.plot: Raylan goes to Memphis to talk to Hot Rod after his men are killed in Mexico, things get tense as Boyd and Darrell wait for the drug shipment, and Boyd and Ava make a deal to get their drugs in prison.

episodes.title: Weight
episodes.plot: Dewey tries to turn his latest score into a ticket out of Harlan. Ava decides to survive on her own in Trambull. Raylan follows Boyd's heroin trail to the Crowes and is introduced to the 21-foot rule.

episodes.title: The Toll
episodes.plot: When Art is shot and is in critical condition, the marshals round up the usual suspects, until an unlikely person confesses. Meanwhile, Ava prepares for the fallout for killing Judith, and Boyd tries to make a new deal with Wynn.

episodes.title: Starvation
episodes.plot: The marshals needs to make a deal with Boyd to take down Darrell Crowe Jr., but Dewey unexpectedly gets in the way. Meanwhile, Ava's enemies in prison begin to make their move against her.

episodes.title: Restitution
episodes.plot: The Mexican cartel catches up with Boyd and demands payback for the dead bodies, Ava goes on the offensive after being accused of snitching, and Wendy faces a hard choice after she learns that Kendal will be tried as an adult.

movies.title: Warrior
movies.plot: During the Tong Wars in the late 1800s, Ah Sahm, a martial arts prodigy from China, immigrates to San Francisco and becomes a hatchet man for the most powerful tong in Chinatown.
filmingLocations: Cape Town Film Studios, Cape Town, Western Cape, South Africa

episodes.title: Exactly the Wrong Time to Get Proud
episodes.plot: Struggling under the pressure of an increased police presence, the Hop Wei search for a new way to survive. Meanwhile, as Leary grows frustrated with his limitations on the city council, the Long Zii gain powerful new connections.

episodes.title: Anything Short of a Blow to the Head
episodes.plot: As Ah Sahm and Young Jun struggle to produce authentic bills, they get valuable printing advice from an unexpected source. Meanwhile, the Secret Service begins to track counterfeit currency and Mai along mingles with a new crowd.

episodes.title: No Time for F*cking Chemistry
episodes.plot: While taking menacing steps to secure Nellie's land, Strickland instills confidence in Leary's political abilities. Then, as the Hop Wei increase bill production, tensions rise between Young Jim and Ah Sahm.

episodes.title: In Chinatown, No One Thinks About Forever
episodes.plot: Shaken by the loss of Nellie's land, Ah Toy grapples with a difficult choice. While Mai Ling strikes a business deal with Eliza, an intrusive encounter echoes Li Yong's fears. Ah Sahm and Yan Mi think on their toes during a police raid.

episodes.title: Whiskey and Sticky and All the Rest Can Wait
episodes.plot: Ah Sahm and Hong race against time to free Young Jun before he's sent to China. As Mai Ling hits rock bottom in prison, Li Yong struggles to gain support for a rescue mission. Buckley raises an ultimatum, and Lee follows his instincts.

episodes.title: A Soft Heart Won't Do You No Favors
episodes.plot: Chao and Lee band together after an unexpected tossup threatens their lives. Meanwhile, the Hop Wei navigate a tense deal with German traders as Leary and Strickland ruffle feathers in the political world.

episodes.title: Gotta Be Crooked to Get Along in a Crooked World
episodes.plot: In the wake of Father Jun's injury, Young Jun steps up for the Hop Wei. As Leary struggles to smooth over rising working-class tensions, Ah Sahm grapples with revelations from Yan Mi and Mai Ling.

episodes.title: You Know When You're Losing a Fight
episodes.plot: As Mai Ling's wedding briefly unites the Hop Wei and Long Zii, Li Yong receives a grim final warning from Kong Pak. Meanwhile, Mosley and Lee further their investigation, Buckley reaps the benefits, and Bill reasserts his dominance.

episodes.title: All of Death Is Going Home
episodes.plot: Ah Sahm makes a bold sacrifice to protect Yan Mi, Mai Ling reckons with the consequences of her actions, and Leary reaches his breaking point after a shocking blow from Strickland.

episodes.title: A Window of F*cking Opportunity
episodes.plot: As the Secret Service finaly corner the Tongs' printing operation, Ah Sahm must choose between his brothers in the Hop Wei anda future with Yan Mi. Later, Young Jun seizes an opportunity to hit the Long Zii where it hurts.

episodes.title: Learn to Endure, or Hire a Bodyguard
episodes.plot: [Cinemax] HD. 'Learn to Endure, or Hire a Bodyguard.' Season 2 Premiere. Ah Sahm takes on new fights; Mai Ling worries about the threat he may pose.

episodes.title: The Chinese Connection
episodes.plot: [Cinemax] HD. 'The Chinese Connection.' (Season 2) Ah Sahm and Young Jun pursue a secretive deal. Penny looks for protection. Mai Ling sends a message.

episodes.title: Not How We Do Business
episodes.plot: Ah Sahm and Young Jun meet a curious recruit. Chao and Mai Ling both have encounters with Zing.

episodes.title: If You Don't See Blood, You Didn't Come to Play
episodes.plot: Ah Sahm's scheme to protect Penny's factory while serving his own covert Hop Wei agenda seems to be working well, but Leary has other plans for the factory that will change things drastically.

episodes.title: Not for a Drink, a F*ck, or a G**damn Prayer
episodes.plot: Penny finds her business in trouble. Leary gets a warning. Bill and Chao put their plot into action.

episodes.title: To a Man With a Hammer, Everything Looks Like a Nail
episodes.plot: [Cinemax] HD. 'To a Man with a Hammer, Everything Looks Like a Nail.' (Season 2) Ah Sahm, Young Jun, and Hong travel with Vega to a fight tournament.

episodes.title: If You Wait by the River Long Enough...
episodes.plot: Change is afoot for the Hop Wei after Father Jun, Ah Sahm, and Young Jun face off. Ah Toy decides that Nellie may be the answer to her problems and takes matters at a sadistic rival brothel into her own hands. Leary is urged by both Buckley and Sophie to utilize his political influence. Just as his heroics are trumpeted, Bill is faced with another swordsman murder. A fatal clash unfolds at the Blake household.

episodes.title: All Enemies, Foreign and Domestic
episodes.plot: [Cinemax] HD. 'All Enemies, Foreign and Domestic.' (Season 2) In search of a killer, the police shut down Chinatown. Buckley steps into a new role.

episodes.title: Enter the Dragon
episodes.plot: [Cinemax] HD. 'Enter the Dragon.' (Season 2) Enemies become allies when chaos erupts in Chinatown.

episodes.title: Man on the Wall
episodes.plot: Young Jun faces a crucial decision after Mai Ling tries to drive a wedge between him and Ah Sahm, who takes the opportunity to go on the offensive against Leary. Resolved to take Buckley down, Penny goes to the press. Mai Ling finally plays her hand against the Hop Wei.

movies.title: Better Call Saul
movies.plot: The trials and tribulations of criminal lawyer Jimmy McGill in the years leading up to his fateful run-in with Walter White and Jesse Pinkman.

episodes.title: Wine and Roses
episodes.plot: Nacho runs for his life. Saul and Kim hatch a plan to mess with Howard. Mike questions his allegiances.

episodes.title: Carrot and Stick
episodes.plot: Kim and Saul enlist some familiar faces in their scheme to get Howard. Harsh realities dawn on Nacho. Gus investigates his suspicions.

episodes.title: Rock and Hard Place
episodes.plot: Still on the run, Nacho is forced to choose where his loyalties lie. Saul must decide whether he wants to remain a "friend of the cartel" after his reputation is called into question. Gus and Mike ready the team for a meet.

episodes.title: Hit and Run
episodes.plot: Despite assurances from the cartel, Gus takes extreme measures to protect himself against looming threats. Kim and Saul enlist the help of a local pro to put on a show for Cliff Main. Howard seeks outside counsel.

episodes.title: Black and Blue
episodes.plot: While business booms for Jimmy, the vise tightens on the cat-and-mouse game between Gus and Lalo.

episodes.title: Axe and Grind
episodes.plot: Kim and Jimmy enlist a knowledgeable contact; Howard scrutinizes Jimmy's business practices.

episodes.title: Plan and Execution
episodes.plot: Jimmy and Kim deal with a last-minute snag in their plan; Lalo is forced to make an unexpected move.

episodes.title: Point and Shoot
episodes.plot: An unexpected visitor forces Jimmy and Kim to face the consequences of their actions.

episodes.title: Fun and Games
episodes.plot: Gus attempts to smooth things over with the cartel while Mike ties up loose ends as Jimmy and Kim deal with the repercussions of their actions.

episodes.title: Nippy
episodes.plot: A lost dog leads to a new friend. A new player gets in the game.

episodes.title: Breaking Bad
episodes.plot: The partners escalate their enterprise to new levels.

episodes.title: Waterworks
episodes.plot: The stakes are raised when a discovery is made that will send shockwaves far and wide.

episodes.title: Saul Gone
episodes.plot: Revelations. Regrets. RICO violations. Jimmy's worlds - and identities - converge in one final showdown.

episodes.title: Magic Man
episodes.plot: Lalo searches for the mysterious Michael. Now doing business as Saul Goodman, Jimmy unveils an unorthodox strategy that tests Kim's tolerance.

episodes.title: 50% Off
episodes.plot: Jimmy's promotional stunt has unintended consequences. Nacho takes extreme measures to earn Lalo's trust. Saul is a success at the courthouse, but still has yet to win Kim over. Simmering with rage and self-loathing, Mike loses his temper.

episodes.title: The Guy for This
episodes.plot: Jimmy's business enters uncharted territory. Kim's confidence is tested when she's faced with a legal problem only she can solve. Nacho navigates increased pressure from Gus. Mike continues to spiral.

episodes.title: Namaste
episodes.plot: As Jimmy doubles down on "Saul Goodman", a deeply conflicted Kim brings him an interesting proposition. Gus makes a sacrifice in order to play the long game. Mike attempts to smooth things over with his family.

episodes.title: Dedicado a Max
episodes.plot: As she and Jimmy grow closer over their campaign to help a client, Kim makes a surprising call; Mike is restless during his out-of-town recuperation.

episodes.title: Wexler v. Goodman
episodes.plot: Kim has a change of heart, but Saul is determined to stick it to Mesa Verde; Mike turns the heat up on Lalo; Nacho attempts to enlist support from above.

episodes.title: JMM
episodes.plot: Jimmy and Kim build a legal firewall with help from Huell; Kim sets things straight with her clients as Jimmy is compromised by his; Gus calms troubled waters in service of his plot to build an empire; Mike does damage control.

episodes.title: Bagman
episodes.plot: When a simple errand for a client goes sideways, Jimmy is pushed to the limit; Mike takes measures to contain the wrath of the cartel; Lalo gets an unexpected visitor.

episodes.title: Bad Choice Road
episodes.plot: In the wake of Jimmy's traumatic misadventure, Kim takes stock of what is important; Jimmy attempts to return to business as usual, but it's more difficult than anticipated; Gus and Mike set a plan in motion.

episodes.title: Something Unforgivable
episodes.plot: Jimmy and Kim make a sideways move that takes a serious turn; Nacho gets closer to the cartel than he'd like.

movies.title: Stranger Things
movies.plot: When a young boy vanishes, a small town uncovers a mystery involving secret experiments, terrifying supernatural forces and one strange little girl.

episodes.title: Chapter One: The Hellfire Club
episodes.plot: Still reeling from the events last year, the gang tries to move on with their lives. However, a threat is brewing both on Earth and the Upside Down.

episodes.title: Chapter Two: Vecna's Curse
episodes.plot: A plane brings Mike to California -- and a dead body brings Hawkins to a halt. Nancy goes looking for leads. A shaken Eddie tells the gang what he saw.

episodes.title: Chapter Three: The Monster and the Superhero
episodes.plot: Murray and Joyce fly to Alaska, and El faces serious consequences. Robin and Nancy dig up dirt on Hawkins' demons. Dr. Owens delivers sobering news.

episodes.title: Chapter Four: Dear Billy
episodes.plot: Max is in grave danger - and running out of time. A patient at Pennhurst asylum has visitors. Elsewhere, in Russia, Hopper is hard at work.

episodes.title: Chapter Five: The Nina Project
episodes.plot: Owens takes El to Nevada, where she's forced to confront her past, while the Hawkins kids comb a crumbling house for clues. Vecna claims another victim.

episodes.title: Chapter Six: The Dive
episodes.plot: Behind the Iron Curtain, a risky rescue mission gets underway. The California crew seeks help from a hacker. Steve takes one for the team.

episodes.title: Chapter Seven: The Massacre at Hawkins Lab
episodes.plot: As Hopper braces to battle a monster, Dustin dissects Vecna's motives -- and decodes a message from beyond. El finds strength in a distant memory.

episodes.title: Chapter Eight: Papa
episodes.plot: Nancy has sobering visions, and El passes an important test. Back in Hawkins, the gang gathers supplies and prepares for battle.

episodes.title: Chapter Nine: The Piggyback
episodes.plot: With selfless hearts and a clash of metal, heroes fight from every corner of the battlefield to save Hawkins - and the world itself.

movies.title: The Office
movies.plot: A mockumentary on a group of typical office workers, where the workday consists of ego clashes, inappropriate behavior, and tedium.

episodes.title: New Guys
episodes.plot: Dwight and Jim are intimidated by the office's newest additions, who are considered younger versions of themselves. Meanwhile, Andy tries to make Nellie's life miserable, and Angela tries to get rid of one of her cats.

episodes.title: Roy's Wedding
episodes.plot: After Roy's wedding, Jim and Pam wonder if they still have any secrets they're hiding from each other. Meanwhile, Clark tricks Erin into a "news audition," and Dwight challenges Nellie's new charity initiative.

episodes.title: Andy's Ancestry
episodes.plot: Nellie plays a trick on Andy after researching his ancestry, Dwight teaches Erin a new language, and Pam tries to teach Nellie how to drive.

episodes.title: Work Bus
episodes.plot: When Jim convinces Dwight that the building is unsafe, Dwight rents a bus and sets up the office inside. Nellie asks for Andy's help in adopting a baby. Meanwhile, Jim tries to make Pam happy with some pie.

episodes.title: Here Comes Treble
episodes.plot: On Halloween, the Cornell a Capella group pays a visit to Andy, Dwight discovers that Nellie takes anxiety pills, and Pam disapproves of Jim's business decision.

episodes.title: The Boat
episodes.plot: Andy has one last chance to captain the family boat before he sells it, Jim, Pam, and Nellie prank Dwight with a radio interview, and Kevin finds out about Oscar's affair with Angela's husband.

episodes.title: The Whale
episodes.plot: The office trains Dwight to sell to a female client without being offensive, only to discover that the client is Jan Levinson. Angela and Oscar both think the senator is cheating on them, and Jim has trouble on an important conference call.

episodes.title: The Target
episodes.plot: Angela orders a hit on Oscar for cheating with her husband, the office makes a tower with their customer complaint cards, Jim wines and dines Stanley and Phyllis in exchange for a favor, and Pam begins her mural.

episodes.title: Dwight Christmas
episodes.plot: Dwight puts together a Pennsylvania Dutch-themed office Christmas party, but he ends it abruptly because Jim has to leave for his other job. Meanwhile, Erin seeks comfort from a co-worker after a disappointing text from Andy.

episodes.title: Lice
episodes.plot: Pam causes a lice outbreak but lets Meredith take the blame, Jim has a business meeting with Dr. J, and some coworkers try to get Darryl and Val back together.

episodes.title: Suit Warehouse
episodes.plot: Dwight and Clark pose as father and son to get an account, Darryl goes for an interview with Jim's new business, and everybody in the office goes crazy over a new espresso machine.

episodes.title: Customer Loyalty
episodes.plot: Dwight tries to keep Darryl from leaving Dunder Mifflin, Jim misses his daughter's recital because of an important business meeting, and Nellie is worried that Erin will dump Andy for Pete.

episodes.title: Junior Salesman
episodes.plot: Dwight gets to hire a new salesman to replace Jim when he is at his other job. But will he promote Clark or go with one of his unqualified friends instead?

episodes.title: Vandalism
episodes.plot: Pam tries to find out who vandalized her mural, Darryl finds out that Jim is a slob, and Oscar and Kevin go to Angela and The Senator's child's first birthday party.

episodes.title: Couples Discount
episodes.plot: Andy returns after three months to an angry office and an even angrier girlfriend, and Jim's Valentines Day with Pam does not go as planned.

episodes.title: Moving On
episodes.plot: Andy finds out that Erin dumped him for Pete, Dwight gets Angela's help taking care of his aunt, and Pam interviews with a real estate firm whose boss is a carbon-copy of Michael Scott.

episodes.title: The Farm
episodes.plot: Dwight's brother and sister return to the farm for an aunt's funeral. Meanwhile, Todd Packer returns to make amends to his former co-workers, but Pam is skeptical.

episodes.title: Promos
episodes.plot: The release of the documentary promos creates tension for the Dunder Mifflin employees, Dwight considers a business venture with his girlfriend's family, and Jim and Darryl have an awkward business meeting with baseball player Ryan Howard.

episodes.title: Stairmageddon
episodes.plot: Dwight shoots Stanley with a bull tranquilizer after he refuses to go on a sales call, Jim and Pam head to marriage counseling, The Senator comes out of the closet, and Andy tries to find a talent agent.

episodes.title: Paper Airplane
episodes.plot: The employees hold a paper airplane competition, Andy gets an acting role in a workplace safety video, and Jim and Pam's marriage tensions continue to build.

episodes.title: Livin' the Dream
episodes.plot: Dwight becomes regional manager after Andy quits his job, Jim dedicates more time to his Dunder Mifflin job to save his marriage, and Angela has problems with her new living arrangements after her breakup with The Senator.

episodes.title: A.A.R.M.
episodes.plot: Dwight prepares for a marriage proposal and hires an assistant for his assistant, Andy auditions for a singing program, Darryl tries to leave his job without a fuss, and Pam has second thoughts about Jim staying in Scranton.

episodes.title: Finale
episodes.plot: One year later, Dunder Mifflin employees past and present reunite for a panel discussion about the documentary and to attend Dwight and Angela's wedding.

episodes.title: The List
episodes.plot: New Dunder Mifflin CEO Robert California leaves a piece of paper with a line down the middle that has names of the Scranton staff on either side of it, leading everyone to try and figure out what it means.

episodes.title: The Incentive
episodes.plot: Under pressure from Robert to increase branch sales, Andy offers an incentive program to the sales staff, which backfires on him when he offers a very personal grand prize.

episodes.title: Lotto
episodes.plot: After the entire warehouse staff wins the lottery and quits their job, Darryl becomes depressed and demands to be fired. Meanwhile, the office staff is forced to load the truck for their orders themselves.

episodes.title: Garden Party
episodes.plot: Andy claims to be throwing a garden party at Dwight's farm to impress Robert California, but he's really doing it to win the approval of his parents, who appear to favor his younger brother.

episodes.title: Spooked
episodes.plot: Erin is worried that she is about to get fired after she organizes a disastrous office Halloween party for Robert and his son. Meanwhile, Robert probes the minds of the employees to come up with the perfect spooky story.

episodes.title: Doomsday
episodes.plot: Dwight installs a "Doomsday Device" on the office computers that could get everyone fired if they make too many mistakes, while Gabe tries to hit on one of Darryl's warehouse employees.

episodes.title: Pam's Replacement
episodes.plot: A pregnant and insecure Pam tries to prove that Jim is attracted to her temp replacement, and Robert and his musician friends take over a jam session with Andy, Kevin, and Darryl.

episodes.title: Gettysburg
episodes.plot: Andy decides to motivate and inspire everyone by taking them on a field trip to Gettysburg. Some people in the office stay behind and Robert California asks them to come up with Dunder Mifflin/Sabre's next big idea.

episodes.title: Mrs. California
episodes.plot: Robert brings his wife to the office so that she can find a job, but he gives Andy conflicting messages about whether to hire her. Meanwhile, Dwight opens a gym in the building and tries to persuade Darryl to join.

episodes.title: Christmas Wishes
episodes.plot: Andy tries to make this year's Christmas the best ever by granting each person's holiday wishes. Meanwhile, Robert California tries to drown his sorrows at the office party.

episodes.title: Trivia
episodes.plot: Andy hopes to make up for a sales deficiency by entering and winning a bar trivia competition, while Dwight flies to corporate headquarters in Florida to demand a management interview with Robert.

episodes.title: Pool Party
episodes.plot: Robert throws a party for the Dunder Mifflin staff at his house before he sells it because of his divorce. At the party, Erin and Dwight agree to flirt with each other to make Andy jealous, and Jim tries in vain to duck out early.

episodes.title: Jury Duty
episodes.plot: Jim gets caught in a lie about his week of "jury duty," and new questions emerge when Angela gives birth to a "premature" baby.

episodes.title: Special Project
episodes.plot: Andy puts Dwight in charge of a special project in Tallahassee, but Dwight doesn't like the team Andy's assembled for him. Meanwhile, Darryl tries to figure out the meaning of Val's Valentine's gift.

episodes.title: Tallahassee
episodes.plot: Dwight refuses to let appendicitis get in the way of leading his new team in Tallahassee, while Andy decides to step in for Erin as secretary in the office.

episodes.title: After Hours
episodes.plot: In Tallahassee, Dwight and Todd Packer try to romance Nellie to get the VP position, while Jim wonders if Kathy is trying to hit on him. Back in Scranton, Val's boyfriend shows up with a message for Darryl.

episodes.title: Test the Store
episodes.plot: Dwight and his team get ready for the grand opening of the Sabre Store, while Andy makes Toby teach self-defense to the Scranton branch employees after he is beat up in the parking lot by a girl.

episodes.title: Last Day in Florida
episodes.plot: Jim tries to warn Dwight that he's going to be fired after Robert rejects the Sabre Store idea, but he refuses to listen. Meanwhile, Darryl and Toby try to sell cookies to Kevin, and Erin tells Andy she's not coming back from Florida.

episodes.title: Get the Girl
episodes.plot: Andy goes to Tallahassee to tell Erin that he loves her and needs her to return to Scranton. Meanwhile, Nellie shows up in Scranton and tries to claim Andy's manager position by offering everyone raises.

episodes.title: Welcome Party
episodes.plot: Andy tries to break up with his girlfriend after going to Florida to declare his love for Erin, and the office employees are forced against their will to throw a party for the hated Nellie.

episodes.title: Angry Andy
episodes.plot: Andy and Erin return to Dunder Mifflin, only to discover that Nellie has taken his job and office and refuses to give them up. Meanwhile, Ryan becomes jealous after Pam tries to play matchmaker for Kelly.

episodes.title: Fundraiser
episodes.plot: Andy confronts Robert for the first time after losing the manager position and quitting his job at a fund raiser sponsored by Angela's husband.

episodes.title: Turf War
episodes.plot: Dwight and Jim fight with the Syracuse over a client after Robert shuts down the Binghamton branch, and Andy sees an opportunity for revenge. Meanwhile Robert tries to figure out the contents of a drunken voicemail to Nellie.

episodes.title: Free Family Portrait Studio
episodes.plot: With former CEO David Wallace's help, Andy launches a plan to get revenge on the Scranton branch. Meanwhile, Dwight launches his own plan to find out if he's the father of Angela's baby.

movies.title: Supernatural
movies.plot: Two brothers follow their father's footsteps as hunters, fighting evil supernatural beings of many kinds, including monsters, demons, and gods that roam the earth.
filmingLocations: Buntzen Lake, Anmore, British Columbia, Canada

episodes.title: Back and to the Future
episodes.plot: Picking up where we left off last season, Sam, Dean and Castiel are left to defend the world after all the souls in hell have been released and are back on Earth and free to kill again.

episodes.title: Raising Hell
episodes.plot: Dean, Castiel and Sam call on Rowena to help keep the evil souls at bay and get an unexpected assist by Ketch.

episodes.title: The Rupture
episodes.plot: Sam and Dean, together with Rowena, work tirelessly to keep all of hell from breaking loose; Castiel cannot forgive an arrogant betrayal.

episodes.title: Atomic Monsters
episodes.plot: Sam and Dean investigate the mysterious death of a girl and the disappearance of another.

episodes.title: Proverbs 17:3
episodes.plot: Sam and Dean's routine case turns out to be anything but.

episodes.title: Golden Time
episodes.plot: Sam and Dean are visited by an old friend; Castiel investigates the disappearance of a local teen.

episodes.title: Last Call
episodes.plot: Dean goes off on his own to take on a case. Meanwhile, Castiel has an idea of how he can help Sam track down God.

episodes.title: Our Father, Who Aren't in Heaven
episodes.plot: Sam, Dean and Castiel's continued search for a way to defeat Chuck leads them to unexpected places and toward unlikely allies.

episodes.title: The Trap
episodes.plot: Sam and Eileen are faced with the brutal truth. Meanwhile Dean and Cass work together in the hopes of getting a step ahead of Chuck.

episodes.title: The Heroes' Journey
episodes.plot: Sam and Dean hit the road to help an old friend, but it appears that their luck may have finally run out and they are the ones who may be in need of rescue.

episodes.title: The Gamblers
episodes.plot: Dean and Sam press their luck in a winner-takes-all game of pool. Meanwhile, Castiel hunts down a would-be murderer, but not for reasons one might think.

episodes.title: Galaxy Brain
episodes.plot: Sam and Dean respond to a frantic call and assist in an extraordinary and heartbreaking rescue; Billie surprises everyone with a visit to the bunker.

episodes.title: Destiny's Child
episodes.plot: A search for the one thing that may give the Winchesters an edge against God leads Sam and Dean to Jo's door and to a secret that may have died with Ruby; Castiel asks Jack to do the unthinkable to help the brothers in their quest.

episodes.title: Last Holiday
episodes.plot: Dean and Sam discover a wood nymph living in the bunker who is determined to protect her "family", at any cost.

episodes.title: Gimme Shelter
episodes.plot: Castiel and Jack work a case involving members of a local church. Meanwhile, Sam and Dean go off in search of Amara.

episodes.title: Drag Me Away (From You)
episodes.plot: Sam and Dean are asked to investigate the murder of a childhood friend, calling them back to a hotel from their past and perplexing the brothers with a case they thought was solved a long time ago.

episodes.title: Unity
episodes.plot: Dean hits the road with Jack who needs to complete a final ritual in the quest to beat Chuck; a difference of opinion leaves Sam and Castiel behind looking for answers to questions of their own.

episodes.title: Despair
episodes.plot: With the plan in full motion, Sam, Dean, Castiel and Jack fight for the good of the common goal.

episodes.title: Inherit the Earth
episodes.plot: Everything is on the line as the battle against God continues; a familiar face returns to join the fight.

episodes.title: Carry On
episodes.plot: It's the final ride for saving people and hunting things.

episodes.title: Stranger in a Strange Land
episodes.plot: Sam enlists everyone's help in trying to track down Dean, who can literally be anywhere. Meanwhile, Castiel may be in over his head after meeting up with an unreliable source. After being drained of his grace, Jack is adjusting to life as a human, learning new skills and figuring out how he fits in to this world of hunters.

episodes.title: Gods and Monsters
episodes.plot: Sam finds a clue to Dean's whereabouts, so he, Mary and Bobby set out to investigate. Castiel imparts some sage advice on Jack, who, still desperate to belong, seeks out a familial connection.

episodes.title: The Scar
episodes.plot: Still trying to solve the mystery of what happened to Dean, Sam enlists the help of Sheriff Jody Mills who may unknowingly already be on the case. Castiel continues to be a father figure to Jack, who surprises even himself, when a life is on the line.

episodes.title: Mint Condition
episodes.plot: Dean continues to struggle, and then Sam has to think when action figures come to life and Dean finds himself inside a real life horror movie.

episodes.title: Nightmare Logic
episodes.plot: After a hunt gone wrong leaves Maggie's whereabouts unknown, Sam, Dean, Mary and Bobby race to find her, but what they find are their own worst nightmares.

episodes.title: Optimism
episodes.plot: Sam and Charlie team up to get to the bottom of a string of random disappearances; Jack believes that he has found a case and convinces Dean to partner with him on the hunt.

episodes.title: Unhuman Nature
episodes.plot: Sam and Castiel track down a Shaman who may be able to help a friend. Nick continues to spiral down a dark path as he looks for answers surrounding the deaths of his wife and son. Jack turns to Dean for help enjoying the human experience.

episodes.title: Byzantium
