movies.title: Sex and the City
movies.plot: Four female New Yorkers gossip about their sex lives (or lack thereof) and find new ways to deal with being a woman in the late 1990s.

episodes.title: To Market, to Market
episodes.plot: Carrie has overslept and rushes like crazy though bogged-down traffic, for she has the honor to open Wall Street by ringing the bell, and has her first 'official' date with Jack Berger, but takes the girls' advice to date simultaneously, notably graphic designer Applegate, a disaster. Miranda finally admits being in love with Steve, baby Brady's father. Charlotte tests Harry's determination not to marry a non-Jew, but even sex fails. Samantha is happy in her sexy neighborhood, where a Pottery Barn looks more out of place than SM leather, and notices the incredibly ...

episodes.title: Great Sexpectations
episodes.plot: Carrie is taken with her romantic Berger, except when it comes to taking her in bed, and admits it to the other girls in the vegan restaurant where the cooking is so light it deserves the name Raw (but restaurant?)- where Samantha dragged them just because the waiter is too hot to miss out on. Charlotte announces her unshakable intention to convert to Judaism in order to become eligible to marry Harry, but finds the rabbi most reticent. Miranda, rejected by Steve, stakes her substitute love life on a state of the art video recorder, but technology can break down, ...

episodes.title: The Perfect Present
episodes.plot: Carrie finally sees Berger's apartment, and likes it but hears it's the work of his ex Lauren, just as his sleeping sounds machine. Big suddenly phones her from California. Charlotte aces her Judaism classes, but is shocked that she must abandon all Christian traditions, even Christmas trinkets. Miranda's ex, Steve, has a new girlfriend, Debbie, so she accuses him of neglecting his paternal duties, perhaps angry after she declared her love and he rejected her. Samantha has sex with the Raw waiter at a crazy would-be designers handbag party, which gets him fired. When ...

episodes.title: Pick-a-Little, Talk-a-Little
episodes.plot: Charlotte is shocked and Berger slightly embarrassed when Samantha enthusiastically explains how she enjoys role-plays with her sexy actor Jerry "Smith" Jerrod, including fake rape. Miranda is relieved when he says a man not calling her back just means not interested, as men don't send sexual double messages. When Carrie can't help herself and criticizes a futile detail in Berger's book, even though she loves it, he shuts down; Samantha cuts of Jerry when he confesses being in AA; both couples soon make up. Charlotte makes her first sabbath a grand production- her ...

episodes.title: Lights, Camera, Relationship
episodes.plot: Carrie drags Berger along shopping to Prada, and brags with a check from her publisher for success in Europe, but learns then her publisher dumped both her supervisor Courtney and Berger; when he takes her on a rather wild bike ride, she freaks out. Miranda still wrestles with her feelings for Steve; Charlotte feels like a basket case after Harry dumps her. When Samantha learns Jerry has dropped his waiter job to do a terribly bad paying play outside Manhattan, he can only lure her to it by promising hot sex afterward. She decides to help him by doing its PR, based on...

episodes.title: Hop, Skip, and a Week
episodes.plot: Carrie finds being an 'irreplacable' freelance writer is not an excuse to dodge jury duty. After her break-up with Harry, Charlotte keeps going to synagogue alone, where Jewish ladies swarm to match her to their eligible sons, but she dishes neither till Harry reappears. Berger is fed-up with disloyal Carrie and the girls' attitude men are always wrong, so he decides to take a break from her in the Hamptons. Miranda is made to understand at the law firm her maternal distraction won't be pardoned; at home Brady seems to feel neglected too. Samantha launches Smith's ...

episodes.title: The Post-It Always Sticks Twice
episodes.plot: The quartet's morning meeting hears counterbalancing news: Charlotte is elated to show her engagement ring from Harry while Carrie, infuriatingly pissed off, is determined not to make the day 'the day she got broke up with a post-it', as Berger chose this excessively succinct medium to beat her to the dumping line. Samantha takes the girls to a new club called 'Bed' where Miranda, who just discovered because of being too busy to eat she can fit into her skinny jeans once again, meets a nice man, Peter. Carrie drags everyone out after having lectured Berger's friends ...

episodes.title: The Catch
episodes.plot: Vogue sends Carrie to report on the latest fitness craze, trapeze 'flying', and she's hooked. Charlotte and Harry prepare for her second perfect wedding, helped by Anthony. Harry's funny friend Howie gets on with Carrie, but in bed drills like a rabbit. Steve wants his girlfriend Debbie to meet Miranda, who hides under the bed to avoid meeting her. Charlotte's big day seems ruled by Murphy's - rather than rabbinic - law: her picture in the paper and her dress in synagogue are stained, Samantha's diamond bracelet falls to pieces...

episodes.title: A Woman's Right to Shoes
episodes.plot: Carrie has no luck at a baby shower: Stanford snatched the last good gift from the list, and host Kyra makes everybody take off their shoes. Carrie's Manolos disappear and Miranda insists she should be compensated. Kyra offers to pay for them until she finds out they cost $485. She claims the shoes are an irresponsible waste and will only pay $200. While she grumbles singles don't get any gifts after graduation, Samantha learns even her bravado is helpless when it comes to children. Miranda meets and instantly falls for handsome new upstairs neighbor Dr. Robert Leeds....

episodes.title: Boy, Interrupted
episodes.plot: Carrie agrees to a reunion to see how her high-school crush -whom she dumped- is, and finds Jeremy got even more attractive. Back in hot Manhattan Samantha can't get through the waiting list for Soho House club which has a pool with service, but picks up someone's (Annabelle Bronstein's) forgotten pass. When Stanford has paraded his hunk Marcus in front of Charlotte and Anthony, the latter proves with a photo from Honcho magazine that the stud used to work as a gay escort named Paul, Charlotte shows it to Miranda at the Knicks game in Madison Square Gardens where they...

episodes.title: The Domino Effect
episodes.plot: Carrie hears Big is in New York to get a 'routine' heart operation and fears for his life; sharing his convalescence makes them close again, but not for long. Miranda is getting on with her neighbor & boyfriend Dr. Robert Leeds, enough to take her first true day off work ever to spend in bed with him- just then Steven burst in and is so surprised by the doc's butt that he butts himself a bloody nose, which gets under control the Knicks way: with a tampon. Now Smith is back, Samantha instructs him sexy manipulations, but can't handle holding hands. Charlotte is seeing ...

episodes.title: One
episodes.plot: When Carrie follows Charlotte to a performance by a woman in Chelsea who speaks nor eats, she meets famous Russian painter and sculptor Aleksandr Petrovsky, who is intrigued by Carrie's cavalier attitude. Samantha, who bravely announces she is 45 and getting glasses, tries to rejuvenate herself by an intimate hair-coloring after finding gray down there, which proves disastrous. Charlotte gets pregnant but has a miscarriage and is plunged into depression until she finds inspiration in a TV documentary on Liz Taylor. After Robert declared his love on a cookie, Miranda ...

episodes.title: Let There Be Light
episodes.plot: After three weeks, Carrie gets a written invitation from Aleksandr; they start flirting and end up in bed. Charlotte looks for a new perfume and a volunteer career while waiting for another pregnancy. Miranda would be happy back with Steve, but keeps bumping into unforgiving yesterday's perfect man Robert. Samantha didn't feel like accompanying Smith to a Teen Girl party- till she reads it's hosted by her ex Richard Wright; she tells Smith they should each play with their own friends, but is greatly relieved to find him waiting for her anyway.

episodes.title: The Ick Factor
episodes.plot: Miranda and Steven exchange good intentions and she proposes to him, instantly sealed with a kiss; the girls wonder what to buy her, not too domestic etcetera. Carrie admires Aleksander's piano playing and poetry reading but isn't really comfortable with such old-fashioned romancing; however a dress from his personal friend Oscar de la Renta sets her glowing. Charlotte and Harry enjoy a romantic French restaurant, but the digestion proves a waking nightmare. Samantha feels, after seeing her photos in a magazine report on Smith, she may need bigger, but still tasteful ...

episodes.title: Catch-38
episodes.plot: Carrie feels extremely welcome with Aleksandr when he spontaneously gives her keys and even the alarm code, which she can't remember. When the girls hear Miranda and Steve are going on a a honeymoon - according to Sam, 'sex with room service' - they offer to babysit Brady. The first watch goes to Carrie, who thus finds out Aleksandr has had a 22-year daughter in Paris and neither wants nor can sire another; Charlotte has him next, and panics when the baby sees her intimate with Harry. When Samantha's male gynecologist sort of suggests her childlessness contributed to ...

episodes.title: Out of the Frying Pan
episodes.plot: After eating at restaurants of various exotic nationalities, Aleksandr decides to cook in Carrie's apartment, where he sees and kills a mouse. What she really cannot handle is his insistence to be open about death, even from breast cancer, while she insists on avoiding the subject. The girls try to make visit time in Samantha's hospital room resemble cocktail hour. Ever-competitive Charlotte learns none of her eggs are good, again, but meets King Charles Spaniel show dog Princess Dandyridge Brandywine, who fails because of a shorter leg, and Charlotte decides ...

episodes.title: The Cold War
episodes.plot: Carrie is embarrassed to be presented to Aleksandr's artistic friends now that he's getting another Paris exposition and enjoys four cold days in his apartment. Miranda is grumpy during their move to Brooklyn, but Steve delivers in every respect. Samantha and Smith Jerrod invite Stanford and Marcus out - the Tattle Tale columnist prints a rumor that Smith is gay; Sam won't have that undo her rep, so she releases a sex tape with Smith online. Big is calling Carrie again but she deletes his messages. Charlotte is enamored with her puppy, and decides to enter her in a ...

episodes.title: Splat!
episodes.plot: Carrie finally has a chance to present everybody to Aleksandr at a dinner, but he's rather aloof and drops the bombshell that he expects her to move with him to Paris for good. Samantha and Charlotte act supportive after some questions, but Miranda doesn't hide she's dead against the idea. Enid invites Carrie to a party, and asks her to bring Aleksandr and a friend of his for her. However she rejects graying food critic Martin Grable as an elderly 'hobbit', dumps him on Carrie and argues the fishing pond for her age group is so small that Carrie's relationship with ...

episodes.title: An American Girl in Paris: Part Une
episodes.plot: Just when Carrie is almost ready to leave for Paris for good, Mr. Big shows up in his limousine - yet she walks away from him for her last dinner with the girls, where Charlotte cries and Miranda makes up. Samantha has her personal input, from nature and experience, concerning a cancer benefit. Once in Paris, Carrie loves the city, but doesn't love sharing Petrovsky's love with his bratty daughter Chloé and his time with his obligations as busy artist. After a disastrous day shopping, her confidence is down like her credit card limit and she loses her "Carrie" ...

episodes.title: An American Girl in Paris: Part Deux
episodes.plot: Carrie has lunch with Petrovsky's ex Juliette B. who tells her he always gives priority to his art above his partner- she finds that true and has a generally bad time. Charlotte prepares with Anthony to receive her promised adoption baby's birth parents, but those changed their mind; ultimately she and Harry get another baby girl from China. Steve's ma Mary suffers memory loss after a mild stroke, and Miranda offers to take her in, which their maid Magda calls love. Samantha finally admits that Smith means enough to her, unlike any other man, to be jealous. Mr. Big ...

episodes.title: Anchors Away
episodes.plot: Miranda is determined not to become a mental full-time-mother, but the reality of breastfeeding is inescapable. Charlotte blurts out to believe the theory everyone only gets two great loves. Carrie is alone but determined to enjoy the countless forms of entertainment in New York, even claiming she's in love with the unpredictable city. After three weeks of calls from Richard, Samantha is out for revenge, and in public. Fortunately it's fleet week, when the city swarms with USNavy boys, who invite the non-moms to a hot party.

episodes.title: Unoriginal Sin
episodes.plot: Samantha's announcement she's giving Richard another chance after his unfaithfulness, as nobody's perfect and it was 'only sex', is such a bomb-shell that even Charlotte makes an obscene gesture. Although Miranda is atheist, she can't deny Steve's entire Catholic family having the baby baptized. Just when Carrie felt down having to write about relationships without having one herself, she gets invited by a publisher to select some of her columns as a book. Eternally positive Charlotte drags Carrie along to the Fountain of Faith, but stands up to say faith didn't ...

episodes.title: Luck Be an Old Lady
episodes.plot: Carrie is bored as if there was no entertainment anywhere in New York, so she insists on celebrating Charlotte's 36th birthday together; Samantha had promised Richard to join him to Atlantic City, but when she tells him he invites the whole quartet to the Taj Mahal casino. Miranda and Carrie, who came to get her, miss his private jet because Steve is really afraid to take care of Brady for more then two hours, till Magda offers to help. Once there, Charlotte lives it up and Miranda switches between gambling and getting ready for bed, but Samantha can't handle the fact...

episodes.title: Cover Girl
episodes.plot: When Carrie is shown the all too naked cover her publishers planned for her columns book, she's shocked, it just screams hooker, so she turns to Samantha who accepts to do her PR for peanuts. Charlotte swallows her pride to seek hope in another advice book. Miranda goes to Weight Watchers where she hooks up with a dieting man, but sugar and fat are aphrodisiacs, sex works up more appetite... Carrie walks in just when Sam is given her hunky courier a blow job, and is judged implicitly too judgmental about it. Stanford present her his hunky new lover Marcus Adante, a ...

episodes.title: Plus One Is the Loneliest Number
episodes.plot: Samantha supervises Anthony at the preparations for Carrie's book presentation party. At her publishers, she meets another author, Jack Berger; they hit it off and have a lovely day. However, only when she invites him to the book party does he decline because he reveals that his girlfriend's family is visiting then. Miranda tells her hot lover Walker Lewis about her baby at the party, then they have sex, but Bradys crying sets him running. Charlotte is finally ready for a real relationship again, and has another perfect suitor: Justin Anderson III. However, when they ...

episodes.title: Critical Condition
episodes.plot: Miranda feels a double failure as neither motherhood nor professional life can get her full attention, and her neighbors give her dirty looks about her screaming baby. Samantha feels her own problems, such as a broken vibrator, are no less important, and demonstrates her expertise on the subject in the shop. Carrie encourages Samantha to acknowledge that Miranda is now a mother, and Samantha eventually offers to babysit Brady while Miranda goes to her hairdresser. When Charlotte feels uncomfortable talking tough with her attractive lawyer about Bunny's divorce terms ...

episodes.title: The Big Journey
episodes.plot: Since Samantha is bored with the city enough to rename it "Same York", Carrie invites her along to her book-signing, a long train journey to San Francisco- alas it's less of the Oriental Express than the New York Sub: tiny 'de luxe' quarters and men who are faithful to their wives. Charlotte and her lawyer who dropped off the last divorce papers at her hard-kept place, which she now considers selling, end up having sex in his apartment. In Frisco, Carrie is mortified to be the opening act for a canine TV puppet, but finally finds a sex partner: Mr. Big, who came to ...

episodes.title: I Love a Charade
episodes.plot: The women head to the Hamptons for the wedding of a flamboyant lounge singer; Charlotte's affair with her lawyer takes an interesting turn.

movies.title: Dark Winds
movies.plot: Follows Leaphorn and Chee, two Navajo police officers in the 1970s Southwest that are forced to challenge their own spiritual beliefs when they search for clues in a double murder case.
filmingLocations: Monument Valley Navajo Tribal Park - U.S. 163 Scenic, Oljato-Monument Valley, Navajo Nation, Arizona, USA

episodes.title: Na'nilkaadii
episodes.plot: Tribal Policeman Joe Leaphorn investigates the death of a man involved in a mysterious cult, while Jim Chee, moonlighting as a PI, works a case of his own. When the investigations collide, Leaphorn and Chee find themselves in grave danger.

episodes.title: Wonders of the Unknown
episodes.plot: Leaphorn explores personal ties to an increasingly mysterious case; Chee is questioned by a reluctant Sgt. Manuelito; the discovery of a body sends Leaphorn and Manuelito in pursuit of a child in danger.

episodes.title: Antigonish
episodes.plot: After facing off with a dangerous man, Chee strikes out on his own; Leaphorn and Manuelito partner with the sheriff's department, leading Leaphorn to identify a vital clue.

episodes.title: The March
episodes.plot: Leaphorn risks his life in pursuit of a suspect; Manuelito stands up to the sheriff in a bid to rescue her boss; seeking answers on a case, Chee considers a dangerous proposition.

episodes.title: Black Hole Sun
episodes.plot: With his suspect in custody, Leaphorn races against the clock to get a confession while Chee goes under cover at the cult that ties their investigations together; Manuelito counsels a teenager who is nervous about the draft.

episodes.title: Monster Slayer
episodes.plot: Joe Leaphorn, Jim Chee and Officer Manuelito are trying to solve the murder of an Old man and a young girl. He has to try to connect the present to the past while dealing with some pretty "dark winds" at the same time.

episodes.title: The Male Rain Approaches
episodes.plot: Leaphorn and Chee interview the witness to the motel murders; Manuelito investigates a new crime.

episodes.title: K'e
episodes.plot: Leaphorn's niece celebrates her Kinaaldá as Leaphorn retrieves the bodies of the murder victims; Manuelito and Chee investigate the whereabouts of the missing Mormon family.

episodes.title: Hooghandi
episodes.plot: Leaphorn suspects all of the crimes on the reservation are related; there is a big break in the case; Leaphorn invites Chee over for dinner; Manuelito makes a discovery of her own.

episodes.title: Ha'íínlni
episodes.plot: With a major suspect in custody, Leaphorn discovers that there is more to this crime than he would have ever imagined; Manuelito faces her worst fears; Chee must make a choice between his career and his people.

episodes.title: HózhóoNaasháa
episodes.plot: Leaphorn, Chee and Manuelito descend on the hiding place of the Buffalo Society, only to be confronted with hard decisions that could change the outcome of the rest of their lives.

movies.title: Dopesick
movies.plot: The series takes viewers to the epicenter of America's struggle with opioid addiction, from the boardrooms of Purdue Pharma, to a distressed Virginia mining community, to the hallways of the DEA.

episodes.title: First Bottle
episodes.plot: Richard Sackler begins to launch a powerful new painkiller, a rural doctor is introduced to the drug, a coal miner plans her future, a DEA agent learns of black market pills and federal prosecutors decide to open a case into OxyContin.

episodes.title: Breakthrough Pain
episodes.plot: OxyContin is on the market but faces a potential threat, Purdue's vast influence reaches the town of Finch Creek, Bridget steps outside her DEA authority and the criminal investigation of OxyContin begins.

episodes.title: The 5th Vital Sign
episodes.plot: Doctor Finnix begins to take Betsy off OxyContin, Bridget sees the toll the it's taking on communities, Rick and Randy investigate the world of "pain societies" and, with sales climbing, Richard Sackler makes bigger plans for his new drug.

episodes.title: Pseudo-Addiction
episodes.plot: Sky-high OxyContin sales are threatened by reports of abuse, prosecutors investigate a claim central to OxyContin marketing, and Finnix begins to question the safety of the drug.

episodes.title: The Whistleblower
episodes.plot: With OxyContin abuse spreading across the country, Bridget brings the fight to Purdue while Rick and Randy seek to find a whistleblower within Purdue to tie their case together.

episodes.title: Hammer the Abusers
episodes.plot: Richard Sackler faces a catastrophic challenge to Purdue's bottom line, Bridget takes her fight to the FDA, Finnix reassesses his life as Betsy struggles to kick her addiction, and Rick and Randy find a bombshell piece of evidence.

episodes.title: Black Box Warning
episodes.plot: Richard Sackler and Purdue work the system to prevent their drug from being reined in, Bridget has a breakthrough in her mission, Betsy has hit rock-bottom while Finnix explores new avenues, and Rick and Randy ready their criminal case.

episodes.title: The People vs. Purdue Pharma
episodes.plot: Rick and Randy's criminal investigation now threatens Richard Sackler's empire, activists take action against Purdue, and Finnix tries to heal his beloved community that's been ravaged by addiction.

movies.title: Criminal Minds
movies.plot: A group of criminal profilers who work for the FBI as members of its Behavioral Analysis Unit (BAU) using behavioral analysis and profiling to help investigate crimes and find the suspect known as the unsub.

episodes.title: Just Getting Started
episodes.plot: When a family annihilator abducts a teen girl, the BAU works the case on either side of the country to save her. But an unlikely connection to a mysterious kit leads to a bigger investigation and at the center of it is Penelope Garcia.

episodes.title: Sicarius
episodes.plot: Team hunts an UnSub who severs spinal cords, and uncover a clue from their last case pointing to a serial killer network. To figure out how big this network is, Rossi must convince a reluctant Garcia to return to the BAU.

episodes.title: Moose
episodes.plot: At the heart of the serial network is Elias Voit. Dangerous psychopath. Manipulative narcissist. Loving father and husband. The team must find all of his kill kits, but one is missing, and the path leads to a bomb in the capitol.

episodes.title: Pay-Per-View
episodes.plot: The BAU hunts for the next connection to the serial killer network when they pursue a home invasion team. Alvez and Garcia convince Tyler Green to submit to a cognitive interview to unlock his memories of Sicarius.

episodes.title: Oedipus Wrecks
episodes.plot: A surprising connection forces Dep. Dir. Bailey to ask the BAU to take a case involving young DC socialites bitten by a sadistic UnSub. When the case turns political, the BAU finds themselves in the crosshairs of a high-powered senator.

episodes.title: True Conviction
episodes.plot: The aftermath of the explosion threatens to end the Sicarius case unless the BAU can justify a reason to keep it open. The hunt takes them to a death row inmate - but is he a killer or another one of Sicarius' victims?

episodes.title: What Doesn't Kill Us
episodes.plot: With the fate of the Sicarius investigation hanging in the balance, the BAU takes a case in West Virginia, where an UnSub practices his own twisted form of Old Testament vengeance.

episodes.title: Forget Me Knots
episodes.plot: Voit's internal struggles with himself lead him to a desperate kidnapping. But Rossi's obsession brings the BAU closer to the truth than they've ever been.

episodes.title: Memento Mori
episodes.plot: Rossi will go to any lengths to prove that Elias Voit is Sicarius; Voit turns Rossi into his own worst enemy, putting his future at the BAU in jeopardy.

episodes.title: Dead End
episodes.plot: With Rossi in Voit's clutches, he grapples with the limits of his technical know-how and mental strength. As the BAU tightens their grip on Voit, he reveals just how far he's willing to take his deadly crusade.

movies.title: Law & Order: Special Victims Unit
movies.plot: This series follows the Special Victims Unit, a specially trained squad of detectives in the New York City Police Department that investigate sexually related crimes.
filmingLocations: Pier 59 Studios, Chelsea Piers, Pier 59 - West 18th Street & West Side Highway, Chelsea, Manhattan, New York City, New York, USA

episodes.title: Gimme Shelter - Part Two
episodes.plot: Benson and Stabler assist in the case of a young girl's shooting and realize it's more than a typical homicide.

episodes.title: The One You Feed
episodes.plot: A group of teens terrorizing tourists has the SVU squad working overtime; McGrath teams them up with the Bronx gang unit to track down a crucial lead.

episodes.title: Mirror Effect
episodes.plot: Benson tries to help a pop star in a volatile relationship; Rollins struggles with taking the stress of work home with her; Fin teaches a rookie a lesson in respecting fellow officers.

episodes.title: The Steps We Cannot Take
episodes.plot: A home invasion and kidnapping leads the SVU to a shocking discovery. Muncy tries to fit in with the squad.

episodes.title: Breakwater
episodes.plot: A young man asks the SVU for help when he suspects his boss is preying on his sister; Velasco tries to convince a reluctant witness to testify in court.

episodes.title: Controlled Burn
episodes.plot: A workaholic is raped after joining her boss to a shady elite party.

episodes.title: Dead Ball
episodes.plot: When the case against a popular sports star falls through, Benson digs into the suspect's past to uncover additional victims; Velasco is disappointed when he meets one of his heroes.

episodes.title: A Better Person
episodes.plot: The SVU hunts for a violent suspect who killed a detective's child; Rollins ponders a potential opportunity.

episodes.title: And a Trauma in a Pear Tree
episodes.plot: Carisi and Rollins work together on an important arraignment. Benson tries to make Noah's Christmas wish come true when a case falls in her lap.

episodes.title: Jumped In
episodes.plot: When Benson becomes the target of a ruthless gang leader, Capt. Duarte takes the case; Fin works with the Bronx SVU to help clear its case backlog; Lt. Dixon offers to translate when a deaf student is raped.

episodes.title: Soldier Up
episodes.plot: While Benson tries to help the gang member who attacked her, Duarte reveals a shocking piece of evidence in the case. Fin is tasked with hiring new detectives for the Bronx SVU.

episodes.title: Blood Out
episodes.plot: As Benson and Carisi put a vengeful crime boss on trial, Fin tries to help a woman who was drugged and left for dead; Velasco takes drastic action to get information from a witness.

episodes.title: Intersection
episodes.plot: A car accident leads the detectives on a search for an ambulance driver assaulting his charges; Fin gives Detective Bruno a tour of Manhattan SVU.

episodes.title: Dutch Tears
episodes.plot: A recently released convict goes looking for his arresting officer, Fin Tutuola; Carisi tries to get an arrest warrant without a positive suspect ID.

episodes.title: King of the Moon
episodes.plot: A man with dementia confesses to murder, but Benson and Carisi believe there's more to the case; when rumors swirl around the squad room, Fin presses Velasco for the truth.

episodes.title: The Presence of Absence
episodes.plot: An internet dating site becomes the source of terror for a young widow; Muncy struggles with Velasco's absence.

episodes.title: Lime Chaser
episodes.plot: The search for a suspect who drugs women's drinks in crowded bars leads the SVU to Muncy's brother; Churlish makes a risky move to impress Benson.

episodes.title: Bubble Wrap
episodes.plot: A construction tycoon interferes with an SVU investigation into her family. Carisi struggles to get an indictment when the complainant backs down.

episodes.title: Bend the Law
episodes.plot: Carisi must tread carefully when Maxwell's husband becomes a person of interest in an SVU investigation. Benson sends Velasco to take an old friend into custody.

episodes.title: Debatable
episodes.plot: Benson tries to help a student after she's assaulted on a field trip. Fin suspects a witness in the case may not be telling the whole truth.

episodes.title: Bad Things
episodes.plot: Benson and Carisi are baffled when a series of assaults have the same M.O. but different DNA at each crime scene. Muncy believes Elias Olsen has struck again and is determined to prove it.

episodes.title: All Pain Is One Malady
episodes.plot: In the search for a revenge-for-hire crime ring, Benson and Stabler combine forces on a case that has now spread globally. Fin and Bruno help a rape victim assaulted a second time. Jet's plan to hack the dark web backfires and puts the team in danger.

episodes.title: And the Empire Strikes Back
episodes.plot: As the investigation into a sex-for-housing scheme expands, Benson's loyalty to Garland is tested. Rollins and Carisi try to keep their witnesses on board when a powerful congressman is identified as a suspect.

episodes.title: Never Turn Your Back on Them
episodes.plot: The search for a missing witness leads Fin and Kat down a dangerous path; Chief McGrath puts pressure on Garland and Benson to get a conviction.

episodes.title: I Thought You Were on My Side
episodes.plot: Benson and Rollins must contend with the FBI and the Organized Crime bureau when a rape victim identifies a dangerous mobster as her assailant.

episodes.title: One More Tale of Two Victims
episodes.plot: The SVU searches for a serial rapist who preys on mothers with young children. Benson and Fin struggle under the tightened reins of Chief McGrath.

episodes.title: Fast Times @TheWheelhouse
episodes.plot: The SVU faces the fury of social media fans when they arrest two popular influencer brothers.

episodes.title: The Five Hundredth Episode
episodes.plot: Amaro and Olivia's ex-boyfriend Burton Lowe ask SVU for help with overturning a wrongful conviction in one of Cragen's old cases.

episodes.title: They'd Already Disappeared
episodes.plot: An investigation into missing sex workers leads SVU to a horrifying discovery.

episodes.title: Nightmares in Drill City
episodes.plot: A fringe, possibly trafficked 17-year-old leads her rap crew to a rival's hideout under the guise of a hookup text. Homicide gets involved, and her mere involvement vs. masterminding come to question.

episodes.title: People vs. Richard Wheatley
episodes.plot: Carisi tries Richard Wheatley for the murder of Kathy Stabler. Benson finds herself at odds with a friend when Barba agrees to take the case.

episodes.title: Silent Night, Hateful Night
episodes.plot: The squad is called in to investigate a wave of hate crimes on Christmas Eve. Amanda catches up with an old flame.

episodes.title: Burning with Rage Forever
episodes.plot: A boy disappears after meeting up with an online gamer. Benson suspects her son is being bullied.

episodes.title: Tommy Baker's Hardest Fight
episodes.plot: When a popular fighter doesn't show up for the biggest bout of the year, Rollins and Velasco are drawn into a complicated web of secrets. McGrath confides in Benson.

episodes.title: If I Knew Then What I Know Now
episodes.plot: A young woman learning about her birth parents asks Benson for help. Carisi and Rollins weigh the risks of publicly disclosing their relationship.

episodes.title: Video Killed the Radio Star
episodes.plot: Benson investigates allegations against a popular radio personality. Rollins goes undercover when a shocking confession leads to another crime.

episodes.title: Promising Young Gentlemen
episodes.plot: Carisi's niece helps a friend report a sexual assault; Benson investigates a college's secret society that preys on female students.

episodes.title: Sorry If It Got Weird for You
episodes.plot: The creator of a dating app is accused of using it to rape women; Velasco's experience as an SVU detective is put on trial.

episodes.title: Once Upon a Time in El Barrio
episodes.plot: Velasco asks Benson for help finding three girls who were trafficked from his hometown to New York City.

episodes.title: Eighteen Wheels a Predator
episodes.plot: Rollins and Fin investigate an assault in Kentucky that has striking similarities to that of a victim found in Central Park; Benson receives intel that turns the case upside down.

episodes.title: Tangled Strands of Justice
episodes.plot: Garland asks Benson to reopen a missing persons case he worked as a rookie officer. A victim in one of Carisi's recent cases is arrested.

episodes.title: Did You Believe in Miracles?
episodes.plot: When a student's school reports a girl missing, the squad must track down a trusted family friend for answers. Benson gets a Mother's Day surprise.

episodes.title: Confess Your Sins to Be Free
episodes.plot: When the only evidence in a crime is a church confession, Carisi must find another way to prove his suspect guilty. Benson agrees to meet with an old friend seeking to make amends for past transgressions.

episodes.title: A Final Call at Forlini's Bar
episodes.plot: The SVU provides help and protection for a longtime domestic violence victim, but when she winds up at the defendant's table in court, Rollins surprises Carisi with a formidable opponent at trial.

movies.title: The Blacklist
movies.plot: A new FBI profiler, Elizabeth Keen, has her entire life uprooted when a mysterious criminal, Raymond Reddington, who has eluded capture for decades, turns himself in and insists on speaking only to her.

episodes.title: The Night Owl
episodes.plot: Six months after Wujing's escape from custody, Reddington secretly resurfaces in Manhattan midst an explosion. When a ex Blacklister is found at the scene, the Task Force begins to investigate a larger conspiracy at game.

episodes.title: The Whaler (No. 165)
episodes.plot: The Task Force works to infiltrate a high-stakes poker game tied to Wujing with the help of new team member Siya Malik. Red and Cooper have opposing tactics when Agnes is bullied at school.

episodes.title: The Four Guns (No. 199)
episodes.plot: An assassination attempt on Sen. Panabaker leads the Task Force to a group of renowned pickpockets; Red sends a dangerous gift to an old friend in custody.

episodes.title: The Hyena (No. 200)
episodes.plot: Red attempts to secure a late financier's fortune locked by a series of challenging clues. When a deadly assassin pursues the money, the Task Force bands together to protect the endowment's rightful heirs..

episodes.title: The Dockery Affair
episodes.plot: An investigation surrounding the murder of a judge sheds new light on an unsolved case. Red's relationship with a trusted colleague is put in a precarious position when his cooperation with the FBI is disclosed.

episodes.title: Dr. Laken Perillos (No. 70): Conclusion
episodes.plot: When Dr. Laken Perillos resurfaces to join Wujing's crusade against Red, a member of The Task Force is put in danger.

episodes.title: The Freelancer (No. 145): Pt. 2
episodes.plot: The return of The Freelancer unveils a conspiracy involving a local photographer; Ressler hits a personal milestone.

episodes.title: The Troll Farmer (No. 38): Pt. 2
episodes.plot: The Task Force investigates a series of social media conspiracies that simulate dangerous public attacks. When a top-secret government program is stolen, the team works to uncover the Troll Farmer's involvement.

episodes.title: The Troll Farmer (No. 38): Pt. 3
episodes.plot: The Task Force races against the clock to recover a valuable asset stolen from the government. Red hatches a plan to help track down the perpetrators.

episodes.title: The Postman (No. 173)
episodes.plot: After an inmate opens fire at a high-security prison, the task force investigates a contraband smuggler known as The Postman. Cooper revisits his past ties to the suspect.

episodes.title: The Man in the Hat
episodes.plot: When Red is identified as a possible hostage during a deli robbery in Philadelphia, Dembe and Ressler take action. Back in D.C., Senator Panabaker evaluates the task force's dealings with Red while Siya digs deeper into her mother's past.

episodes.title: Dr. Michael Abani (No. 198)
episodes.plot: Dembe reflects on his complicated past when he receives a concerning call from an old connection. An ambitious Congressman begins to question the Task Force's operations.

episodes.title: The Sicilian Error of Color
episodes.plot: While accompanying Red on a series of abnormal tasks, Siya learns more about Meera's past. Congressman Hudson attempts to persuade a powerful friend to join his crusade against the task force.

episodes.title: The Nowhere Bride (No. 192)
episodes.plot: The Task Force investigates the whereabouts of a missing newlywed. Red offers his help to a powerful cartel leader while Siya visits a connection from her mother's past.

episodes.title: The Hat Trick
episodes.plot: In an effort to prove their worth to Congressman Hudson, Red provides The Task Force with three criminal cases that are deeper than they appear. Ressler helps a friend make amends.

episodes.title: Blair Foster (No. 39)
episodes.plot: When a corrupt lawyer is linked to a string of corporate cover-ups, Red helps the team investigate her operation; Sen. Panabaker and Cooper await a judge's decision on the fate of the task force.

episodes.title: The Morgana Logistics Corporation (No. 167)
episodes.plot: The task force encounters a ring of fraudulent companies shipping contraband around the world; Congressman Hudson's investigation escalates when he recruits help.

episodes.title: Wormwood (No. 182)
episodes.plot: Red's attempt to mediate a meeting between two rival families takes a deadly turn; when an elusive criminal is linked to the incident, the task force races against time to save Red and his associates.

episodes.title: Room 417
episodes.plot: A cryptic tip from Red leads the task force to uncover a security breach within the U.S. government; Congressman Hudson takes major steps to uncover the inner workings of the task force.

episodes.title: Arthur Hudson
episodes.plot: Cooper is caught on the defensive when summoned by the Attorney General. Red visits dear friends.

episodes.title: Raymond Reddington (No. 00): Pt. 1
episodes.plot: Series finale, part 1. Under pressure from Congressman Hudson's investigation, the Task Force must try to anticipate Reddington's next move.

episodes.title: Raymond Reddington (No. 00): Good Night
episodes.plot: Series finale, part 2. The future of the FBI's Reddington Task Force is decided.

episodes.title: The Skinner (No. 45)
episodes.plot: Following Elizabeth Keen's death, Reddington and the task force have disbanded, with Red's whereabouts unknown. But when one of their own is injured in the line of duty, they are drawn back together to bring down a global conspiracy.

episodes.title: The Skinner (No. 45): Conclusion
episodes.plot: A kidnapping poses a test for the capabilities of the Task Force as they contend with a mysterious pirating organization.

episodes.title: The SPK (No. 178)
episodes.plot: A new case involving stolen artifacts reunites Red with a former Blacklister. Aram faces a difficult decision.

episodes.title: The Avenging Angel (No. 49)
episodes.plot: The Task Force races to locate a Blacklister who uses any means necessary to return what has been unjustly stolen. Ressler asks Park for a favor. Cooper tries to piece together an event for which he has no memory.

episodes.title: Benjamin T. Okara (No. 183)
episodes.plot: Dembe's position as an FBI agent causes complication for Red as the task force handles a case involving military technology. Cooper and Park each find their personal lives increasingly complicated.

episodes.title: Dr. Roberta Sand, Ph.D. (No. 153)
episodes.plot: The task force investigates a therapist who may be the key to the resurgence of a crime family. Red bonds with Agnes.

episodes.title: Between Sleep and Awake
episodes.plot: In a series of flashbacks, Donald Ressler recalls his actions in the aftermath of Elizabeth Keen's death.

episodes.title: Dr. Razmik Maier (No. 168)
episodes.plot: The death of a professional tennis player leads the Task Force to a doctor who may be fixing the odds for a major sports betting syndicate. Red digs deeper into Dembe's betrayal. Ressler struggles with sobriety.

episodes.title: Boukman Baptiste (No. 164)
episodes.plot: A spate of coordinated attacks on Red's lieutenants puts Dembe in imminent danger, prompting him to relive the events that led him to join the FBI two years earlier.

episodes.title: Arcane Wireless (No. 154)
episodes.plot: The Task Force's investigation into Arcane Wireless, an untraceable cellular network for criminals, leads to unexpected consequences. Red races against the clock to get a colleague out of trouble.

episodes.title: The Conglomerate (No. 142)
episodes.plot: An investigation into the Conglomerate, a group of former government-sponsored assassins, becomes complicated when the task force learns one of its own has ties to the group. Red digs deeper into the events leading to Liz's death.

episodes.title: The Chairman (No. 171)
episodes.plot: The Task Force pursues the Chairman, who operates a dark web stock market trading shares of criminal organizations. Red takes extreme measures to locate a tracking device, causing Ressler to spiral. Cooper contacts with his blackmailer.

episodes.title: Genuine Models Inc. (No. 176)
episodes.plot: The task force is led to an unusual suspect when the clients of an escort service start turning up dead. Red and a friend try to recover an item after reuniting at a friend's memorial.

episodes.title: Eva Mason (No. 181)
episodes.plot: While searching for Senator Panabaker's missing daughter-in-law, the task force learns there may be a larger pattern of abductions. Red continues to piece together the mystery behind Liz's death.

episodes.title: Andrew Kennison (No. 185)
episodes.plot: Tensions rise when Cooper's search for his blackmailer overlaps with the Task Force's latest Blacklist case; Kennison admits to designing the tracking device which Liz ingested, but we so far do not learn how she came to do so.

episodes.title: Helen Maghi (No. 172)
episodes.plot: Red chases a lead that could shed light on both Liz's death and Cooper's blackmailing. The task force experiences a major shake up when one of its own is arrested.

episodes.title: El Conejo (No. 177)
episodes.plot: When a member of the task force is captured by the leader of a cartel, they turn to Red for guidance; Red investigates a seemingly impossible heist.

episodes.title: Laszlo Jankowics (No. 180)
episodes.plot: Red questions the whereabouts of a former associate; the task force hunts down a criminal dealing in illegal psychedelics.

episodes.title: The Bear Mask
episodes.plot: Feeling the weight of recent pressures, Aram turns to an unusual outlet for release.

episodes.title: Caelum Bank (No. 169)
episodes.plot: In an effort to reveal his true enemy, Red turns to the Task Force to help ground a flying fortress bank.

episodes.title: Marvin Gerard (No. 80): Conclusion Pt. 1
episodes.plot: Red and the Task Force spring into action after learning who betrayed them.

episodes.title: Marvin Gerard (No. 80): Conclusion Pt. 2
episodes.plot: Red and Cooper square off with conflicting endgames for their mutual traitor; a major secret about the task force falls into the wrong hands.

movies.title: Friends
movies.plot: Follows the personal and professional lives of six twenty to thirty year-old friends living in the Manhattan borough of New York City.

episodes.title: The One After Joey and Rachel Kiss
episodes.plot: Joey and Ross both attempt to come clean to each other that they're dating Rachel and Charlie. Phoebe finds out Mike has another girlfriend.

episodes.title: The One Where Ross Is Fine
episodes.plot: Rachel and Joey fear for Ross's state of mind after he finds out about their relationship. Chandler and Monica visit some friends of Phoebe to get advice on adoption. Frank and the triplets come to visit.

episodes.title: The One with Ross's Tan
episodes.plot: Ross goes to a tanning salon but fails to follow the 'simple' instructions. Joey and Rachel struggle to make the transition from friends to lovers. Monica and Phoebe try to avoid an annoying woman that used to live in their building.

episodes.title: The One with the Cake
episodes.plot: On Emma's first birthday, Ross and Rachel convince everyone to delay their plans so they can attend her party, however plans go awry when Emma's birthday cake is revealed.

episodes.title: The One Where Rachel's Sister Babysits
episodes.plot: Rachel's sister Amy comes to visit and moves in with her and Joey. Phoebe constantly and accidentally ruins Mike's proposals. Joey struggles to write a letter of recommendation for Monica and Chandler's adoption agency.

episodes.title: The One with Ross' Grant
episodes.plot: Ross applies for a paleontology grant and finds out Charlie's ex-boyfriend reviews the applications. Monica and Rachel fight over who has to take Phoebe's ugly painting.

episodes.title: The One with the Home Study
episodes.plot: Monica and Chandler nervously prepare for a visit from an adoption worker. Phoebe and Mike keep changing their minds about donating their wedding money to charity. Ross fights Rachel's fear of swings.

episodes.title: The One with the Late Thanksgiving
episodes.plot: Joey, Ross, Rachel and Phoebe convince Monica and Chandler to host Thanksgiving, however the four of them end up arriving to dinner an hour late.

episodes.title: The One with the Birth Mother
episodes.plot: Nervous and excited, Monica and Chandler travel to Ohio to meet a young pregnant woman, Erica Simmons, who is considering allowing them to adopt her child when it's born.

episodes.title: The One Where Chandler Gets Caught
episodes.plot: Monica & Chandler look at real estate outside the city which leads to the rest of the gang reminiscing on all their memories of the apartment.

episodes.title: The One Where the Stripper Cries
episodes.plot: Old secrets come to light when Ross and Chandler attend a college reunion. Monica and Rachel throw Phoebe a bachelorette party. Joey appears as a celebrity partner on a game show.

episodes.title: The One with Phoebe's Wedding
episodes.plot: Chaos ensues as Phoebe and Mike prepare to get married.

episodes.title: The One Where Joey Speaks French
episodes.plot: Phoebe tries to teach Joey to speak French for an audition; Ross and Rachel head out to Long Island after her dad has a heart attack.

episodes.title: The One with Princess Consuela
episodes.plot: Phoebe ponders whether or not to changer her name. Monica & Chandler take Joey to visit the new house. Ross & Rachel set their eyes on their career profession.

episodes.title: The One Where Estelle Dies
episodes.plot: Ross tries to get Rachel to go back to Ralph Lauren, Joey doesn't know that his agent has died, and Monica and Chandler bump into Janice.

episodes.title: The One with Rachel's Going Away Party
episodes.plot: The gang throws Rachel a goodbye party, during which she says goodbye to everybody individually.

episodes.title: The Last One
episodes.plot: Phoebe races Ross to the airport in a bid to stop Rachel from leaving for Paris. Monica and Chandler pack up their apartment ahead of their move to their new house, and Joey buys Chandler a new chick and duck as a leaving present.

episodes.title: The One Where No One Proposes
episodes.plot: Rachel, Ross and Joey get together and figure out that no one was actually going to propose; Mr. Geller walks in on Monica and Chandler having sex.

episodes.title: The One Where Emma Cries
episodes.plot: Chandler, having trouble getting enough sleep at home, falls asleep in a meeting and accidentally agrees to run his company's Tulsa office.

episodes.title: The One with the Pediatrician
episodes.plot: Joey arranges a blind date for Phoebe. Chandler is leaving for Tulsa without Monica, because she has got a great job offer.

episodes.title: The One with the Sharks
episodes.plot: Monica thinks Chandler is sexually attracted to sea life after he switches the station from porn to a shark documentary in order to conceal his sordid viewing.

episodes.title: The One with Phoebe's Birthday Dinner
episodes.plot: Phoebe will celebrate her birthday by having a dinner with her friends at a fancy restaurant. But everybody is late to the dinner, due to a series of problems.

episodes.title: The One with the Male Nanny
episodes.plot: Looking for a new nanny, Ross and Rachel hire a male nanny named Sandy. Monica tells Chandler that a guy at work is the funniest guy she has ever met.

episodes.title: The One with Ross's Inappropriate Song
episodes.plot: Ross finds a way to make Emma laugh - singing "Baby Got Back." Meanwhile, Phoebe meets Mike's parents, and Joey and Chandler find a video tape in Richard's apartment.

episodes.title: The One with Rachel's Other Sister
episodes.plot: Rachel's middle sister shows up at Thanksgiving and causes arguments amongst the gang.

episodes.title: The One with Rachel's Phone Number
episodes.plot: Rachel is ready to start hanging out again. She and Phoebe go to a bar, where they meet two guys.

episodes.title: The One with Christmas in Tulsa
episodes.plot: Chandler must spend Christmas in Tulsa, which Monica thinks he might have an affair with a former Miss Oklahoma runner-up while he is there. Chandler comes home early to announce that he quit his job.

episodes.title: The One Where Rachel Goes Back to Work
episodes.plot: Chandler starts looking for a job and is anxious about having a baby, Rachel decides to go back to work, and Phoebe works as an extra on Joey's show.

episodes.title: The One with Phoebe's Rats
episodes.plot: Ross makes Joey stay away from their new nanny. Mike accidentally kills Phoebe's rat. Gavin gives Rachel a scarf and a kiss for her birthday.

episodes.title: The One Where Monica Sings
episodes.plot: A night at Mike's piano bar gives Monica a very showy moment in the spotlight; Chandler employs his secret skill to repair Joey's botched eyebrow-waxing job.

episodes.title: The One with the Blind Dates
episodes.plot: Phoebe and Joey purposely set Ross and Rachel up on bad dates in the hopes they'll get back together. Monica and Chandler babysit Emma.

episodes.title: The One with the Mugging
episodes.plot: Joey gets a part in a stage-play in a painful way. Ross and Phoebe are mugged outside Central Perk, Phoebe realizes that she mugged Ross 18 years ago. Chandler starts his new career as an advertising writer.

episodes.title: The One with the Boob Job
episodes.plot: When Monica and Chandler both ask Joey for money not wanting the other to know why they are asking for it, Chandler sees that Joey gave money to Monica. Joey makes up that Monica is getting a boob job. Phoebe asks Mike to move in with her, but decides not to when she and Mike argue about their future. Rachel attempts to baby-proof the apartment, but makes Joey go insane when he can't open anything.

episodes.title: The One with the Memorial Service
episodes.plot: When Chandler and Ross joke around on their college website, Ross is accused of being dead which leads to the fact that he was not popular in college. Joey is not willing to give his favorite stuffed animal, Hugsy, to Emma. Monica helps Phoebe not call Mike.

episodes.title: The One with the Lottery
episodes.plot: Hoping to win a huge jackpot, the friends pool their money and buy dozens of lottery tickets. However, they bicker over how to spend the fortune if they win, and Monica irritates everyone else by buying tickets just for her and Chandler.

episodes.title: The One with Rachel's Dream
episodes.plot: Nervous about his upcoming romantic scenes, Joey rehearses them with Rachel. Ross & Chandler get their money's worth on their weekend trip to Vermont while Phoebe takes advantage of Monica's clientele.

episodes.title: The One with the Soap Opera Party
episodes.plot: Joey throws a cast party on the roof of his building where he ends up making out with an attractive professor that Ross had a crush on.

episodes.title: The One with the Fertility Test
episodes.plot: Joey comes to Ross for advice on dating Charlie. Chandler and Monica bump into Janice at a fertility clinic. Rachel has a gift certificate for a massage which Phoebe doesn't want her to use.

episodes.title: The One with the Donor
episodes.plot: Rachel take Joey's girlfriend Charlie and Phoebe shopping. Ross presents his theory to get a chance to go a conference in Barbados. Monica and Chandler consider alternate pregnancy options.

episodes.title: The One in Barbados
episodes.plot: The gang heads down to Barbados for the palaeontology conference.

movies.title: Solar Opposites
movies.plot: A family of aliens move to middle America, where they debate whether life is better there or on their home planet.

episodes.title: The Ping Pong Table
episodes.plot: At their new jobs, Korvo and Terry lobby their boss to get the office a ping pong table.

episodes.title: The Earth Rake (beta)
episodes.plot: Fearing Terry will blow a big client opportunity, Korvo crashes his business trip in the Wooden City.

episodes.title: The Mobile AISHA Emitter
episodes.plot: AISHA goes on a date outside the ship.

episodes.title: The Pronunciation Cassette Tapes
episodes.plot: The Solars get a pet dinosaur.

episodes.title: The Birth-A-Day Present
episodes.plot: It's Yumyulack's birthday.

episodes.title: The Stockiverse Ray
episodes.plot: The Solars get trapped in a Stock Image-filled Stockiverse.

episodes.title: The Cardboard Dead Drop
episodes.plot: An action-filled, espionage action episode that takes place in the wall.

episodes.title: The Super Gooblers
episodes.plot: The Solars all create Super Gooblers, which are living versions of their own emotional problems.

episodes.title: Down and Out on Planet X-Non
episodes.plot: Glen has to learn to survive in an alien city.

episodes.title: The Re-Visibility Bouillabaisse
episodes.plot: Korvo and Terry accidentally turn themselves invisible and the invisibility makes them blind.

episodes.title: The Unwanted Personification of Terry
episodes.plot: The Solars have been on Earth long enough that they're starting to become human.

movies.title: True Detective
movies.plot: Seasonal anthology series in which police investigations unearth the personal and professional secrets of those involved, both within and outside the law.

episodes.title: Episode #4.1
episodes.plot: In Ennis, Alaska, the men that operate a research station vanish. To solve the case, Detectives Danvers and Navarro will have to confront the darkness themselves, and dig into the haunted truths that lie buried under the eternal ice.

episodes.title: The Great War and Modern Memory
episodes.plot: The disappearance of a young brother and sister leads to a frantic search which will haunt one detective for the rest of his life.

episodes.title: Kiss Tomorrow Goodbye
episodes.plot: As the search for Julie continues, the doll discovered at the crime scene provokes a reaction, while Wayne and Roland learn of a potential suspect.

episodes.title: The Big Never
episodes.plot: The search for Julie brings Wayne and Amelia together again, Wayne and Roland retrace their investigation to spot missed clues, while one White Finger resident receives a warning.

episodes.title: The Hour and the Day
episodes.plot: Wayne and Roland investigate possible connections between the local church and the Purcell crimes as tensions in West Finger reach boiling point.

episodes.title: If You Have Ghosts
episodes.plot: In 1980, all hell breaks loose at the home of Woodard, while in the present, Wayne and Roland reconnect after Wayne makes a discovery.

episodes.title: Hunters in the Dark
episodes.plot: In 1990, Wayne and Roland revisit the Purcell case to uncover previously hidden or forgotten clues, while Tom looks for answers and two faces from the past resurface.

episodes.title: The Final Country
episodes.plot: In 1990, following an apparent suicide, the Purcell case is deemed solved, but Wayne and Roland have other ideas, which leads them to a defining course of action.

episodes.title: Now Am Found
episodes.plot: Wayne struggles to hold on to his memories, and his grip on reality, as the truth behind the Purcell case is finally revealed.

movies.title: Harlan Coben's Shelter
movies.plot: The story of Mickey Bolitar and his new life with a mom in rehab, a dead father, an annoying aunt, and a new school in New Jersey.

episodes.title: Pilot
episodes.plot: After a tragic accident, Mickey Bolitar finds himself living with his aunt in Kasselton, New Jersey-a town with a lot of buried secrets. classmate disappears without a trace. Mickey's drawn into a conspiracy so shock.

episodes.title: Catch Me If U Can
episodes.plot: Mickey and his new friends Ema and Spoon investigate Ashley's disappearance. It's dangerous and they talk to sinister people. Mickey's Mom Kitty finally is ready to meet up with Mickey but it's risky. Shira encounters her best friend from high school. The history teacher figures out what happened to Mr. V.

episodes.title: The Dirt Locker
episodes.plot: Ashley is still missing and Mickey is on a mission to find her. Spoon and Ema help him retrace Ashley's last day at school. Sunglasses Man is still following Mickey around in a threatening way. The Bolitars have a family reunion. Rachel and Mickey work together on their history report about The Holocaust. Shira and Hannah talk things through and repair their friendship.

episodes.title: Phantom Threads
episodes.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

movies.title: Shingeki no Kyojin
movies.plot: After his hometown is destroyed and his mother is killed, young Eren Jaeger vows to cleanse the earth of the giant humanoid Titans that have brought humanity to the brink of extinction.

episodes.title: Recap: Since That Day
episodes.plot: A recap of main events in the first 13 episodes.

episodes.title: OVA: Ilse's Notebook
episodes.plot: Hange is insistent on capturing a Titan for the advancement of scientific research, but Erwin is adamant in his refusal to allow it. Will an unexpected discovery during an expedition beyond the walls alter the situation?

episodes.title: OVA: The Sudden Visitor: The Torturous Curse of Youth
episodes.plot: In the year 849, Jean returns home after two years in training. After Jean gets into a dispute with Sasha following a training exercise, Commander Pyxis suggests they settle things in a cooking contest. While they are preparing, unexpected visitor arrive to meet Jean.

episodes.title: OVA: Difficulty
episodes.plot: In the year 848, the recruits are split into two groups for a wilderness exercise to learn how to sustain themselves in times of peace. Marco has trouble leading his group due to the arrogance of both Eren and Jean.That night, the thieves ambush Eren's group, taking Krista hostage along with their equipment. Putting aside their petty squabbles, they must team up together to rescuing Krista.

episodes.title: OVA: No Regrets: Part 1
episodes.plot: How Levi, humanity's strongest soldier, came to be. Find out where Levi originated from and how he came to work in the survey corps.

episodes.title: OVA: No Regrets - Part 2
episodes.plot: The second part of Levi and Erwin's back story together. Levi has decided to join the Survey Corps to avoid his previous crimes but what new challenges will he face and what does Erwin make of Levi? We find out in the second part of the OVA No Regrets.

episodes.title: OVA: Lost Girls: Wall Sina, Goodbye - Part 1
episodes.plot: On the day before the 57th Exterior Scouting Mission, Hitch gives Annie Leonhart the task of finding a missing person, Carly Stratmann, the daughter of a wealthy merchant in Stohess District. She visits the Stratmann family mansion to ask Carly's father, Elliot G. Stratmann, about the circumstances that may be related to her disappearance.

episodes.title: OVA: Lost Girls: Wall Sina, Goodbye - Part 2
episodes.plot: After finding Carly's boyfriend dead, Annie decides to cover up his murder and locate Carly Stratmann to prevent the case from interfering with her mission. On her way back she is kidnapped by two private investigators who've gone rogue.

episodes.title: OVA: Lost Girls: Lost in the cruel world
episodes.plot: Mikasa Ackerman imagines a world where the Titans never invaded the Walls and her parents are not killed by her kidnappers. This Mikasa of an alternate world meets a young boy, Eren Yeager, and learns of his desire to see the outside world.

episodes.title: The Other Side of the Sea
episodes.plot: As Marley battles the Mid-East Alliance to end a four-year war, a group of Warrior candidates on the front lines compete to be the successor of the Armored Titan.

episodes.title: Midnight Train
episodes.plot: Though glad the war is over, Both the Eldian Warriors and Marley brass realize that neither have a future unless they finish the job of retaking the Founding Titan.

episodes.title: The Door of Hope
episodes.plot: A flashback into Reiner's harsh and difficult life, and his own personal wish to become a Marleyan Warrior for his family honor.

episodes.title: From One Hand to Another
episodes.plot: A sudden visit from the Tybur family shakes up the Marleyan military. Meanwhile, Falco smuggles letters for a friend and helps two old comrades reunite.

episodes.title: Declaration of War
episodes.plot: Eren confronts Reiner, while Willy Tybur gives a speech to the entire world in which he aims to solve the endless cycle of hate directed towards Eldians.

episodes.title: The War Hammer Titan
episodes.plot: As the Attack Titan rampages, several people are crushed to death. While all of this is going on, the War Hammer Titan appears to confront Eren.

episodes.title: Assault
episodes.plot: As the battle between Eren and the warriors rages on, another party makes their move on Marley's Forces that pushes the tide of the battle into a more devastating climax.

episodes.title: Assassin's Bullet
episodes.plot: Out of strength, the Armored Titan falls. Furious to have her hometown trampled, Gabi picks up a gun and takes off.

episodes.title: Brave Volunteers
episodes.plot: As Paradis deals with the aftermath of the raid on Liberio, Armin looks back in the past to meeting the volunteer soldiers who reshaped their world.

episodes.title: A Sound Argument
episodes.plot: Two years ago, Paradis welcomed their first visitor who was surprised to see one of their own. Obtaining their help will be critical in a three-part plan to protect Paradis.

episodes.title: Deceiver
episodes.plot: Gabi and Falco escape from prison. Without a clue where they should go, they receive help from none other than the devils they despise. Meanwhile, Floch's mind is shifting gears.

episodes.title: Guides
episodes.plot: A new turn of events rocks the Military Corps. In the midst of confusion, Eren begins enacting his plans for Paradis.

episodes.title: Children of the Forest
episodes.plot: As Zeke's plans come to light and the Jaegerists move in, the two warrior fugitives have their identities uncovered.

episodes.title: Savagery
episodes.plot: As the Jaegerists take over, Eren has a tense altercation with Armin and Mikasa, and Levi battles Zeke.

episodes.title: Sole Salvation
episodes.plot: A look into Zeke's past shows his struggle to become a Warrior. His plans to end the suffering of all Eldians stem from a chance friendship made in his youth.

episodes.title: Above and Below
episodes.plot: With the Jaegerists now in charge, Zeke's master plan is revealed. But before it is put in motion, Eren recruits help to flush out any invaders in their midst.

episodes.title: Judgment
episodes.plot: The Marleyan military's air force invades Paradis, while Eren Yeager continues battling Porco Galliard, who is soon joined by Reiner Braun in his Armored Titan form.

episodes.title: Sneak Attack
episodes.plot: The Beast Titan joins the fray, but General Magath is determined to take him down. Meanwhile, with the city in flames, Colt and Gabi rush to rescue Falco who's held captive by the Jaegerists.

episodes.title: Two Brothers
episodes.plot: Colt pleads with Zeke to not use his scream and turn Falco into a Titan. All the while, soldiers and Titans clash in battle as Eren struggles to make contact with his brother.

episodes.title: Memories of the Future
episodes.plot: Zeke takes Eren through Grisha's memories to show him how he's been brainwashed. But in doing so, Zeke discovers something about Eren that he never knew.

episodes.title: From You, 2000 Years Ago
episodes.plot: Eren and Zeke with their contradicted ethics and shattered emotions, clash on the credibility of their ideals while Ymir, the founder, discloses her tragic past and deepest secrets within the walls.

episodes.title: Thaw
episodes.plot: With no walls left on the island and Shiganshina full of Titans, the Scouts must battle their former comrades. In the midst of it all, Gabi is determined to find and rescue Falco at whatever cost.

episodes.title: Sunset
episodes.plot: The Rumbling is set in motion once all hardening is undone, but this also sets Annie free. As the Jaegerists take control of the island, Connie races towards Ragako to feed Falco to his Titan mother.

episodes.title: Pride
episodes.plot: Upon reaching Ragako, Connie hatches a plan to trick Falco into being eaten by his mother. Elsewhere, hero of the Eldian Empire, Jean, is set to execute Yelena and Onyankopon for their crimes against humanity.

episodes.title: Night of the End
episodes.plot: Deep in the forest, an unlikely rabble of Marley stragglers and island fugitives attempt to set their hatred aside and talk around a campfire without killing each other.

episodes.title: Traitor
episodes.plot: The Azumabito's flying boat is guarded by a port full of Jaegerists, but the Scouts are reluctant to kill their former friends. If they wish to avoid bloodshed, they can't afford their plan to go wrong.

episodes.title: Retrospective
episodes.plot: For the flying boat to take off, the mechanics need half a day to service it. Knowing they'll never last that long with Jaegerist reinforcements on the way, the crew is forced to change their plans.

episodes.title: The Dawn of Humanity
episodes.plot: Regardless of where it all began, Eren commits to his path of destruction during the Scouts' first visit to the Marleyan mainland, leaving Mikasa to wonder if things could've been different.

episodes.title: The Final Chapters: Special 1
episodes.plot: Ramzi and Halil, two refugee children, flee the approaching Colossal Titans as they surround the crowds of refugees. One year prior, Eren reflects on his previous experiences, and his future actions.

episodes.title: The Final Chapters: Special 2
episodes.plot: As Eren approaches Fort Salta, the Alliance arrives to stop the Rumbling and save the world - as the series reaches an epic conclusion.

movies.title: The Crowded Room
movies.plot: In Manhattan in the summer of 1979, a young man is arrested for a shocking crime, and an unlikely investigator must solve the mystery behind it before the true criminal strikes again.
filmingLocations: New York City, New York, USA

episodes.title: Exodus
episodes.plot: Danny Sullivan is arrested for a violent crime. Rya Goodwin probes his troubled past for answers.

episodes.title: Sanctuary
episodes.plot: Rya visits the Ghost House. Danny opens up about his turbulent friendship with Ariana.

episodes.title: Murder
episodes.plot: Danny gets a gift for Ariana. Annabelle returns. Rya pieces together the events leading up to Rockefeller Center.

episodes.title: London
episodes.plot: In the aftermath of the shooting, Danny flees the country to find his father.

episodes.title: Savior
episodes.plot: Danny's and Candy's lives are forever changed by the arrival of an unlikely savior.

episodes.title: Rya
episodes.plot: Rya puts her career on the line to investigate a radical new theory.

episodes.title: The Crowded Room
episodes.plot: Danny finally faces the truth about his crime.

episodes.title: Reunion
episodes.plot: As the trial approaches, Rya and Stan disagree over strategy. Danny struggles to sort through his past.

episodes.title: Family
episodes.plot: The trial is here, as Stan and Patricia, deliver their opening statements Candy has a decision to make.

episodes.title: Judgment
episodes.plot: Season finale. Danny's life hangs in the balance.

movies.title: Secret Invasion
movies.plot: Fury and Talos try to stop the Skrulls who have infiltrated the highest spheres of the Marvel Universe.

episodes.title: Resurrection
episodes.plot: Nick Fury learns of a clandestine invasion of Earth by Skrulls.

episodes.title: Promises
episodes.plot: Fury grapples with past and present.

episodes.title: Betrayed
episodes.plot: Fury uncovers a rebel Skrull plot.

episodes.title: Beloved
episodes.plot: Fury must make some hard sacrifices.

episodes.title: Harvest
episodes.plot: Fury gathers his allies. Gravik deals with unrest.

episodes.title: Home
episodes.plot: All hope for humanity rests on Fury's shoulders.

movies.title: Doctor Who
movies.plot: The further adventures in time and space of the alien adventurer known as the Doctor and their companions from planet Earth.

episodes.title: Doctor Who: Children in Need Special
episodes.plot: Rose must learn to accept the Doctor in his new, regenerated form.

episodes.title: Time Crash
episodes.plot: The Tenth Doctor meets one of his previous incarnations.

episodes.title: The Next Doctor
episodes.plot: The Doctor arrives in London on Christmas Eve in 1851 where he encounters the Cybermen and a man who claims he's a Time Lord called the Doctor.

episodes.title: Planet of the Dead
episodes.plot: A meeting in a London bus with jewel thief Lady Christina takes a turn for the worst for the Doctor when the bus takes a detour to a desert-like planet, where the deadly Swarm awaits.

episodes.title: The Waters of Mars
episodes.plot: In a Mars base the inhabitants are being infected by a mysterious water creature which takes over its victims. The Doctor is thrust into the middle of this catastrophe knowing a larger one is waiting around the corner.

episodes.title: A Ghost Story for Christmas
episodes.plot: This mini-story tells of the Weeping Angels and depicts their abduction of a young woman named Julia Hardwick.

episodes.title: The End of Time: Part One
episodes.plot: The Ood have given a warning to The Doctor. The Master is returning yet that is not the biggest threat. A darkness is coming which brings with it The End of Time.

episodes.title: The End of Time: Part Two
episodes.plot: With almost everyone on Earth now recast in his image, The Master controls the Earth. He's shocked however when he realises one person hasn't changed; Donna Noble. The Doctor soon understands what the pounding in the Master's head is; it's the Time Lords, who are trying to return and re-establish Gallifrey. If they succeed, it'll mean the Last Great Time War will re-start, and all the horrors which came with it. In order to stop Rasillon's mad plan, the Doctor must make a choice. Finally, the Ood's prophecy for the Doctor becomes true, and he takes the TARDIS on a ...

episodes.title: Prequel to the Impossible Astronaut
episodes.plot: The new series of Doctor Who begins with The Impossible Astronaut. But before that we have a short scene written by Steven Moffat that reveals a little of what we can expect from the adventure and what the Doctor will be facing!

episodes.title: Prequel to the Curse of the Black Spot
episodes.plot: The third episode of Doctor Who is a scary, action-packed adventure called The Curse of the Black Spot. What evil lurks for the crew in the darkness? Come aboard and watch the spine-chilling prequel to The Curse of the Black Spot.

episodes.title: Prequel to A Good Man Goes to War
episodes.plot: As the Doctor prepares to face his darkest hour, key players conspire and a grim warning is given...

episodes.title: Prequel to Let's Kill Hitler
episodes.plot: The battle of Demon's Run has been fought but the stakes are now higher than ever! As the TARDIS crosses the universe, the Doctor receives a heart-breaking message from Amy... Their adventure continues in this brilliant Prequel written by Steven Moffat.

episodes.title: Prequel to the Wedding of River Song
episodes.plot: The Doctor's time is running out and he faces a date with death by the shores of Lake Silencio - Meanwhile, in the presence of an old enemy, we hear a prophesy that will change everything.

episodes.title: Prequel to the Doctor, the Widow and the Wardrobe
episodes.plot: Written by Steven Moffat and starring Matt Smith as the Doctor, this exciting Prequel shows what was happening to the Time Lord moments before the explosive start of the Christmas Special!

episodes.title: Prequel to Asylum of the Daleks
episodes.plot: The Doctor receives a message from a mysterious hooded stranger - a woman called Darla Von Karlsen wants to meet him...

episodes.title: The Making of the Gunslinger
episodes.plot: A detailed explanation of the creation of the Gunslinger and all the factors that went into selecting the "participants".

episodes.title: The Great Detective
episodes.plot: Matt and Jenna introduce the Doctor Who Christmas Prequel, The Great Detective, in which Vastra, Jenny and Strax try to persuade the grumpy Doctor to engage again.

episodes.title: Vastra Investigates: A Christmas Prequel
episodes.plot: Madame Vastra finishes a case with Scotland Yard, but continues to worry about The Doctor.

episodes.title: The Bells of Saint John: A Prequel
episodes.plot: A look at the opening of the first episode of the new season, The Bells of Saint John.

episodes.title: The Battle of Demon's Run: Two Days Later
episodes.plot: In the aftermath of the battle of Demons Run, a battle-scarred Strax lies dying on the floor - or has he just fainted...

episodes.title: She Said, He Said: A Prequel
episodes.plot: The Doctor and Clara each deliver a separate monologue summing up their thoughts on each other before the events of "The Name of the Doctor."

episodes.title: Clarence and the Whispermen
episodes.plot: The Whispermen visits Clarence in his cell.

episodes.title: Clara and the Tardis
episodes.plot: Clara has a conversation with the TARDIS, and encounters a surprise.

episodes.title: Rain Gods
episodes.plot: The Doctor and River are about to be sacrificed to the Rain Gods of an unknown planet and the Doctor must come up with a plan to save themselves.

episodes.title: The Inforarium
episodes.plot: In the Doctor's quest to delete all information on him in the universe, he visits the Inforarium, a universal database, in hope to erase himself from it.

episodes.title: The Night of the Doctor
episodes.plot: With the aid of the Sisterhood of Karn, the Eighth Doctor regenerates into the War Doctor.

episodes.title: The Day of the Doctor
episodes.plot: In 2013, something terrible is awakening in London's National Gallery; in 1562, a murderous plot is afoot in Elizabethan England; and somewhere in space an ancient battle reaches its devastating conclusion.

episodes.title: Prologue
episodes.plot: Doctor Who Season 9 starts here with this prologue to Episode 1, "The Magician's Apprentice".

episodes.title: The Doctor's Meditation
episodes.plot: The Doctor contemplates a journey to see an old acquaintance and digs a well.

episodes.title: Friend from the Future
episodes.plot: The Doctor and Bill are chased by a group of Daleks in a short introductory video to present Bill, the new companion, to audiences for the first time.
