episodes.plot: New beginnings abound as Serentiy welcomes Noreen's baby, Isaac's birth mother tells him her whole story, and Erik reveals his painful past to Helen.

episodes.title: The Rules of the Game
episodes.plot: As the recall petition quickly picks up steam, Maddie and Cal attend a black-tie charity fundraiser and Ronnie presses Dana Sue to make up her mind.

episodes.title: Dear Heart
episodes.plot: Friends gather to plan a celebration of life. Meanwhile, counseling is off to a rocky start for Ronnie and Dana Sue, and Isaac meets his birth father.

episodes.title: If Thou Wilt, Remember
episodes.plot: More than margaritas are shaken up as Cal's past resurfaces, an unsavory acquaintance returns to Serenity, and Helen faces a life-changing decision.

movies.title: Cruel Summer
movies.plot: In a small Texas town, popular teen Kate is abducted. Seemingly unrelated, a girl named Jeanette goes from being a sweet, awkward outsider to the most popular girl in town, but by 1995 she has become the most-despised person in Am...

episodes.title: Welcome to Chatham
episodes.plot: In the summer of 1999, small-town computer genius Megan resents the arrival of outgoing and mysterious foreign exchange student Isabella; little does she know how her life will change by the summer of 2000.

episodes.title: Ride or Die
episodes.plot: In Summer 1999, Isabella grows closer to Luke while struggling to connect with Megan; in Winter 1999, Isabella searches for justice following the disastrous Christmas party.

episodes.title: Bloody Knuckles
episodes.plot: In Summer 1999, Megan and Isabella bond during an overnight at the Chambers' cabin; Luke stands up to Brent, but ends up causing more problems for his dad; suspicions are raised after fingerprints are found on the gun that shot Luke.

episodes.title: Springing a Leak
episodes.plot: In Summer 1999, Megan wants to be adventurous and makes fake IDs for the gang; in Winter 1999, a burst pipe leads the Landrys and Isabella to a messy night at the Chambers house; Isabella wishes to help but is met with resistance.

episodes.title: All I Want for Christmas
episodes.plot: In summer 1999, Isabella is rocked by a surprise visit from her past; in winter 1999, Isabella's concerns for Megan lead her to some surprising news; in summer 2000, family loyalties are tested.

episodes.title: The Plunge
episodes.plot: In summer 1999, sparks fly at Luke's birthday party; in winter 1999, relationships are tested as Megan becomes more distant from Luke; in summer 2000, Megan obsesses over an interesting letter she received.

episodes.title: It's the End of the World
episodes.plot: In winter 1999, tensions are high on Y2K; at the New Year's Eve party, a not-so-secret conversation changes the lives of the trio forever; in summer 2000, suspicion falls on Ned after some new evidence from summer 1999 comes to light.

episodes.title: Confess Your Sins
episodes.plot: In summer 1999, new friendships are formed, and secrets are kept as the crew approaches senior year at the annual school car wash; in winter 1999, Megan and Isabella push for answers; in summer 2000, Debbie wants to protect her daughter.

episodes.title: The Miseducation of Luke Chambers
episodes.plot: Luke examines all his relationships and worries that the pressures of being a "Chambers man" have changed him.

episodes.title: Endgame
episodes.plot: As timelines collide, friendships implode, new evidence emerges and the shocking truth is revealed in more ways than one.

episodes.title: Happy Birthday, Jeanette Turner
episodes.plot: Taking place over 3 summers in the 90s when a popular teen goes missing, and a seemingly unrelated girl transforms from a sweet and awkward outlier to the most popular girl in town, eventually becoming the most despised person in America.

episodes.title: A Smashing Good Time
episodes.plot: It's time for the annual Skylin Garden Club Party. Year after year after year, the residents of Skylin struggle with the truth around what happened to Kate, keeping their secrets buried and maintaining appearances.

episodes.title: Off with a Bang
episodes.plot: Victim or villain? Jeanette continues to add fuel to the fire as her reckless behavior causes her friends and family to question her even more.

episodes.title: You Don't Hunt, You Don't Eat
episodes.plot: Kate, reeling from the lawsuit, prepares her defense and finds friendship in an unlikely source. The annual Wallis hunting trip becomes the setting for an important first meeting.

episodes.title: As The Carny Gods Intended
episodes.plot: Jeannette and Kate cross paths at the Skylin High takeover of the County Fair, where one is desperate to prove herself and the other to lose herself.

episodes.title: An Ocean Inside Me
episodes.plot: A new deposition threatens Jeanette's case. A discovery causes Cindy's suspicions about her own daughter to reach new heights as her relationship with Greg becomes further strained.

episodes.title: Happy Birthday, Kate Wallis
episodes.plot: Kate struggles with a family secret she's been holding on to. Joy tries to convince Kate to go on "The Marsha Bailey Show." Mallory has a birthday surprise.

episodes.title: Proof
episodes.plot: On the first day of school, everyone learns that the drama of the summer is anything but over and that some people will pay more for the consequences of Jeanette and Kate's deception than others.

episodes.title: A Secret of My Own
episodes.plot: Kate's closely held secrets and fragmented memories of her time in Martin's captivity are brought to the surface.

episodes.title: Hostile Witness
episodes.plot: Kate and Jeannette's worlds collide as the court date arrives, finally forcing the two young women to answer the question on everyone's mind, but the answer comes with a price that not everyone can pay.

movies.title: The Mandalorian
movies.plot: The travels of a lone bounty hunter in the outer reaches of the galaxy, far from the authority of the New Republic.

episodes.title: Chapter 17: The Apostate
episodes.plot: The Mandalorian begins an important journey.

episodes.title: Chapter 18: The Mines of Mandalore
episodes.plot: The Mandalorian and Grogu explore the ruins of a destroyed planet.

episodes.title: Chapter 19: The Convert
episodes.plot: On Coruscant, former Imperials find amnesty in the New Republic.

episodes.title: Chapter 20: The Foundling
episodes.plot: Din Djarin returns to the hidden Mandalorian covert.

episodes.title: Chapter 21: The Pirate
episodes.plot: The people of Nevarro need protection from rampant pirate attacks.

episodes.title: Chapter 22: Guns for Hire
episodes.plot: The Mandalorian visits an opulent world.

episodes.title: Chapter 23: The Spies
episodes.plot: Survivors come out of hiding.

episodes.title: Chapter 24: The Return
episodes.plot: The Mandalorian and his allies confront their enemies.

episodes.title: Chapter 9: The Marshal
episodes.plot: The Mandalorian is drawn to the Outer Rim in search of others of his kind.

episodes.title: Chapter 10: The Passenger
episodes.plot: The Mandalorian must ferry a passenger with precious cargo on a risky journey.

episodes.title: Chapter 11: The Heiress
episodes.plot: The Mandalorian braves high seas and meets unexpected allies.

episodes.title: Chapter 12: The Siege
episodes.plot: The Mandalorian rejoins old allies for a new mission.

episodes.title: Chapter 13: The Jedi
episodes.plot: The Mandalorian travels to a world ruled by a ruthless magistrate who has made a powerful enemy.

episodes.title: Chapter 14: The Tragedy
episodes.plot: The Mandalorian and Child travel to an ancient site.

episodes.title: Chapter 15: The Believer
episodes.plot: To move against the Empire, the Mandalorian needs the help of an old enemy.

episodes.title: Chapter 16: The Rescue
episodes.plot: The Mandalorian and his allies attempt a daring rescue.

movies.title: The Vampire Diaries
movies.plot: The lives, loves, dangers and disasters in the town, Mystic Falls, Virginia. Creatures of unspeakable horror lurk beneath this town as a teenage girl is suddenly torn between two vampire brothers.
filmingLocations: 598 Abernathy Road, NE, Atlanta, Georgia, USA

episodes.title: Hello, Brother
episodes.plot: Stefan searches tirelessly for Damon and Enzo months after their mysterious disappearance.

episodes.title: Today Will Be Different
episodes.plot: No one can accept the loss of Damons humanity that Enzo hopes for too, Damon carelessly tries to prove everyone wrong.

episodes.title: You Decided That I Was Worth Saving
episodes.plot: As Enzo continues to fight the control over him, Bonnie finds herself at the center of a deadly game and forced to make a heart wrenching decision involving two of the most important people in her life. At the Armory, Alaric researches a mysterious artifact that he hopes will help in their fight to get Damon and Enzo back. Finally, Damon's downward spiral leads him to Tyler Lockwood who attempts to talk some sense into him before it's too late.

episodes.title: An Eternity of Misery
episodes.plot: Meanwhile Alaric and Stefan try to find out about the origins of what they are up to, Damon is searching for an artifact so he travels to Texas where he encounters Peter Maxwell who leads him to a new revelation.

episodes.title: Coming Home Was a Mistake
episodes.plot: Stefan and the others remember what matters most when tragedy strikes close to home.

episodes.title: Detoured on Some Random Backwoods Path to Hell
episodes.plot: When her children become the focus of the Siren's latest plan, Caroline (Candice King) takes drastic measures to ensure nothing gets in the way of keeping her family safe. In a race against the clock, Stefan (Paul Wesley) pledges to do everything he can to save the twins, while tensions between Alaric (Matt Davis) and Caroline boil over, leading them to face some harsh realities about the future of their family. Meanwhile, when Enzo (Michael Malarkey) finds himself unable to fight off Sybil's (guest star Nathalie Kelley) latest move, Stefan dives into his subconscious...

episodes.title: The Next Time I Hurt Somebody, It Could Be You
episodes.plot: Faced with the fallout from his interaction with Cade (Wolè Parks), Stefan (Paul Wesley) is determined to have one thing go right - Christmas Eve with Caroline. However, when Damon (Ian Somerhalder) and Sybil (Nathalie Kelley) crash their Christmas Eve dinner, which had been joined by Alaric (Matt Davis), Matt (Zach Roerig) and Peter (Joel Gretsch), things quickly take a dark and twisted turn. Meanwhile, in a series of flashbacks to Stefan's past, Cade's attempt to entice him with his mysterious agenda leaves Stefan faced with an unimaginable decision. Kat Graham and ...

episodes.title: We Have History Together
episodes.plot: Stefan and Damon attend an anger management support group looking for their next victim. Sybil is still alive and teaching a group of high school students who she'll later use as leverage to get Caroline to locate a historical artifact that can be used against her. Meanwhile, Stefan and Damon continue their commitment to Cade as they test the morals of a young doctor, Tara.

episodes.title: The Simple Intimacy of the Near Touch
episodes.plot: Mystic falls is greeted by a traditional celebration and also two reckless brothers. Caroline remains in denial about the future.

episodes.title: Nostalgia's a Bitch
episodes.plot: Sybil puts Damon in a catatonic state for revenge. Caroline and Bonnie enter Damon's mind and realize Stefan is the key to his fate. Sybil competes with her sister for control of the bell.

episodes.title: You Made a Choice to Be Good
episodes.plot: Cade returns to Mystic Falls with new assignments for Damon and Stefan that each lead to unthinkable consequences.

episodes.title: What Are You?
episodes.plot: Damon makes a deal with Cade to retrieve the Maxwell journal in exchange for Stefan's soul.

episodes.title: The Lies Will Catch Up to You
episodes.plot: Damon and Alaric face an old enemy after finding a weapon that might kill Cade. Stefan is captured by someone from his past. Bonnie tries to reach out to Enzo through Cade.

episodes.title: It's Been a Hell of a Ride
episodes.plot: Damon and Stefan join forces against Cade to protect Elena's casket, while Caroline and Alaric cope with their daughters' growing powers.

episodes.title: We're Planning a June Wedding
episodes.plot: A wedding is quickly planned in order for Damon and Stefan to lure a dangerous enemy out into the open.

episodes.title: I Was Feeling Epic
episodes.plot: With the fate of Mystic Falls at stake, Stefan and Damon must fight their greatest enemy for one last battle.

episodes.title: Day One of Twenty-Two Thousand, Give or Take
episodes.plot: Damon is faced with a new reality without the love of his life; Bonnie decides to be Damon's moral compass, and look out for Alaric, who lost his fiancée. Stefan protects the town from Lily; Enzo must decide who he is loyal to.

episodes.title: Never Let Me Go
episodes.plot: Damon makes a decision that could ruin Lily and Stefan's deal; Alaric needs Bonnie's help with an artifact; Caroline discovers a shocking secret.

episodes.title: Age of Innocence
episodes.plot: In the aftermath of a clever plan orchestrated by Lily, Damon sets off on a road trip with Bonnie and Alaric in search of leverage they can use against his mother. Meanwhile, Caroline, who is being held hostage by the Heretics, learns some shocking information about Valerie's past, while Stefan learns a few unexpected details about his own past from Lily. Finally, Alaric turns to Bonnie for her help after coming clean about a secret he's been keeping.

episodes.title: I Carry Your Heart with Me
episodes.plot: Just as Damon thinks he's gained the upper hand in his fight against Lily, an unexpected turn of events leaves him scrambling for a plan B.

episodes.title: Live Through This
episodes.plot: Bonnie, Damon, and Alaric go through a tough shock with the Phoenix stone, while Caroline sent Stefan to spend the day with his ex, Valerie.

episodes.title: Best Served Cold
episodes.plot: After being reunited with her former love Julian, Lily hosts a dinner party to introduce him to Damon and Stefan and to declare peace between her family of Heretics and the residents of Mystic Falls. Damon and Stefan find themselves at an impasse when they realize they have differing views on how to handle Julian's arrival. At the party, Bonnie and Matt uncover a strange mystery involving some unsuspecting residents, while a devastating revelation causes Alaric to reach his breaking point.

episodes.title: Mommie Dearest
episodes.plot: Damon and Stefan conspire to kill Julian, while Caroline struggles with the fact that she's pregnant with Ric's kids.

episodes.title: Hold Me, Thrill Me, Kiss Me, Kill Me
episodes.plot: It's Nora and Mary Louise's anniversary and Julian has big plans for the night, however, Lily and her sons have even bigger plans for Julian.

episodes.title: Cold as Ice
episodes.plot: In the events following their mother's passing, Stefan and Damon try to engage in the holiday spirit.

episodes.title: Hell Is Other People
episodes.plot: Damon's soul is stuck in the phoenix stone, the world of the phoenix stone is trying to break Damon emotionally and at the same time Damon's family and friends are trying to bring him back.

episodes.title: Things We Lost in the Fire
episodes.plot: Caroline throws a baby shower for Alaric's twins, and the Salvatore brothers face the hallucinations caused by the Phoenix Stone.

episodes.title: Postcards from the Edge
episodes.plot: Stefan uncovers the reason behind Damon's dark descent following his experience in the Phoenix stone.

episodes.title: This Woman's Work
episodes.plot: Vampire hunter Rayna Cruz is on the loose and Damon has to make things right when his actions inadvertently put his loved ones in her path.

episodes.title: Moonlight on the Bayou
episodes.plot: Stefan goes to New Orleans to lure Rayna Cruz away from his friends and comes face to face with Klaus Mikaelson, who's suspicious of his old friend's arrival.

episodes.title: I Would for You
episodes.plot: Tired of having everyone sacrifice themselves for him, Damon decides to leave the group. Meanwhile, Bonnie's new discovery threatens Damon's plans to stop Rayna.

episodes.title: Days of Future Past
episodes.plot: Stefan will find himself with a choice to make and his decision will determine the fates of everyone he cares about, especially Damon.

episodes.title: I Went to the Woods
episodes.plot: In the aftermath of his brother's fateful decision, Stefan awakens to find himself thrown into a life or death situation with only his basic instincts to rely on. With time working against him, he sets off on a journey of survival while forced to confront a lifetime of irreversible damage Damon has done to their relationship. Meanwhile, desperate to save his brother, Damon follows an unusual lead he has come across, while Matt sends Valerie to Dallas to enlist Alaric's help in the search for Stefan. Finally, when Rayna discovers the emergence of a new threat, she sets...

episodes.title: One Way or Another
episodes.plot: Determined to capture an escaped vampire named Ambrose, who may be the key to getting Stefan back safely, Damon heads to Memphis with Alaric in tow. However, reluctant to step back into his former vampire-hunting ways, Alaric makes his unwillingness to participate clear, while revealing the truth about the past three years of his life without Damon. Meanwhile, in the psych ward, Bonnie meets a young woman named Virginia, who provides her with some valuable information about why The Armory may be after her. Finally, Enzo takes matters into his own hands when he learns ...

episodes.title: Somebody That I Used to Know
episodes.plot: When Enzo's efforts to protect Bonnie end up putting her life in jeopardy, they learn that Rayna may hold the key to her survival. With time running out and Rayna at the reins, Enzo and Bonnie reluctantly team up with Damon, who is desperate to save Bonnie's life and to repair their broken friendship. Elsewhere, when Stefan travels to Dallas and comes face to face with Alaric, tensions escalate and they are forced to confront the fallout from Stefan's absence in Caroline's life. Finally, Enzo learns The Armory's true motives behind their search for Bonnie.

episodes.title: Kill 'Em All
episodes.plot: With Bonnie's life at stake and an uphill battle ahead of them, Damon and Enzo lead the charge to save Bonnie before her condition worsens. Stefan reluctantly teams up with Matt for the sake of Bonnie and uncovers the truth behind Matt's anger towards him. Elsewhere, determined to help her best friend, Caroline joins Alaric on a mission and quickly realizes how much she's missed her former supernatural lifestyle. Finally, after their plan takes an unexpected turn, Damon makes a fateful decision that will forever change his relationship with Bonnie.

episodes.title: Requiem for a Dream
episodes.plot: When Damon's risky attempt to save Bonnie takes an unexpected turn, the consequences of his actions forces everyone to band together to help her pull through. Meanwhile, when a new threat leaves Caroline's life in jeopardy, Stefan makes a rash decision that ultimately forces them to face the fallout from their relationship. Elsewhere, Enzo tries to hold it together as he painfully watches Bonnie in the fight of her life, while Matt takes matters into his own hands to save one of his closest friends. Alaric also appears.

episodes.title: Gods and Monsters
episodes.plot: Despite their best efforts to help Bonnie through the harrowing predicament she now faces, Damon, Enzo and Caroline realize their options are running out and drastic measures need to be taken. With their only chance of saving their friend lying inside the Armory, Stefan breaks the news to Caroline that they may need help from an unlikely source - her and Alaric's twin daughters. Elsewhere, Enzo keeps Bonnie preoccupied by bringing her back to their cabin but when his plan takes an unexpected turn, it'll be up to Damon to make the ultimate sacrifice to save his closest...

movies.title: Midsomer Murders
movies.plot: A veteran Detective Chief Inspector and his young Sergeant investigate murders around the regional community of Midsomer County.

episodes.title: The Blacktrees Prophecy
episodes.plot: Deep in Blacktrees Forest is a bombproof shelter built by a man named Warren Kaine. His extreme paranoia has drawn other survivalists to the village, and now a doomsday prepper group meets weekly.

episodes.title: The Debt of Lies
episodes.plot: Gated estate Challis Court is a tight-knit community for retired police officers, but when a new arrival is found dead, the other residents regard the murder as an affront; Barnaby realizes that the killer is likely an ex-police officer.

episodes.title: A Grain of Truth
episodes.plot: A trendy organic bakery in a restored mill is causing resentment amongst several villagers. Causton CID don't take the complaints too seriously until several people are dosed with a dangerous hallucinogenic. Then the first death occurs.

episodes.title: Dressed to Kill
episodes.plot: Parish chairwoman Lois Springfield is found dead in a local theatre. The detectives assume it's because of her hostility toward a drag show being organised, but other motives are at play.

episodes.title: The Wolf Hunter of Little Worthy
episodes.plot: After a local photographer wins an urban myth competition with his creation of The Wolf Hunter, it unexpectedly gains a cult following. However, when a man is killed, Barnaby must investigate if this myth has become murderous reality.

episodes.title: The Stitcher Society
episodes.plot: A local outcast, who was controversially acquitted of murder years previously, is the latest inductee into a post-operative heart rehab club. Following his arrival, members' dreams of a second chance at life begin being cut short.

episodes.title: Happy Families
episodes.plot: DCI Barnaby and DS Winter are called in to investigate the death of Victor Karras, a manufacturer of exclusive board games, who appears to have been poisoned.

episodes.title: Scarecrow Murders
episodes.plot: A scarecrow festival to raise church funds takes a grisly turn when dead bodies are found staged like the festival's straw creations. Barnaby's investigation uncovers more going on than a simple competition.

episodes.title: For Death Prepare
episodes.plot: The Midsomer Mummers, an amateur opera company, is in the middle of rehearsals for a charity concert, when a dead body is found in the theatre. The aim of the inquiry will be to find out who is most desperate to be the centre of attention.

episodes.title: The Witches Of Angel's Rise
episodes.plot: When a body is found surrounded by ritual symbols on the eve of a Psychic Fayre, Barnaby must step into the spiritual world of mediums, psychics, and occult followers to find the killer.

movies.title: Vikings
movies.plot: Vikings transports us to the brutal and mysterious world of Ragnar Lothbrok, a Viking warrior and farmer who yearns to explore--and raid--the distant shores across the ocean.
filmingLocations: Ballyhenry Studios, Ashford, Co Wicklow, Ireland

episodes.title: The Saga of Ragnar Lothbrok
episodes.plot: Ubbe Lothbrok tells the story of his legendary Father Ragnar Lothbrok, how we went from a farmer to King.

episodes.title: The Saga of Lagertha
episodes.plot: Ivar the Boneless summons the Seer to tell him about his greatest enemy, Lagertha. The Seer takes us through Lagertha's epic story in the previous 4 seasons, telling everything there is to know about the formidable warrior, fearless leader, and legendary shield-maiden.

episodes.title: The Saga of Bjorn
episodes.plot: On the run after being defeated by Ivar the Boneless in Kattegat, Torvi tells her son the story of his legendary father, Viking warrior and explorer Bjorn Ironside, to ensure their family legacy lives on.

episodes.title: The Saga of Floki
episodes.plot: After leaving Kattegat, Ivar the Boneless embarks on a journey to unknown places, where he stumbles upon a stranger and suddenly remembers previous memories, which forces him to recall the story of the unique genius that is Floki.

episodes.title: New Beginnings
episodes.plot: Bjorn struggles with the responsibilities of kingship and finds he can't rely on his mother, Lagertha; she has other plans. Ivar falls into the hands of Kievan Rus, and in their ruthless and unpredictable ruler, Prince Oleg, he may finally have met his match.

episodes.title: The Prophet
episodes.plot: Messengers arrive in Kattegat with news that presents Bjorn with a dilemma. As Bjorn attempts to do the right thing as ruler of Kattegat, Prince Oleg of Kiev seems untroubled by his conscience.

episodes.title: Ghosts, Gods and Running Dogs
episodes.plot: Lagertha is forced to take action; In Kiev, although Oleg continues to be friendly, Ivar is aware of the threat which Oleg poses to the vulnerable young heir to the throne; Bjorn has answered the call and come to the aid of an old enemy.

episodes.title: All the Prisoners
episodes.plot: Lagertha leads her village's response to the recent attacks but despite her best efforts, when the inevitable attack comes, the consequences are tragic. Olaf has a bold new plan for the future of Norway. In Kiev, although Ivar discusses Oleg's ambitions for Scandinavia, he's actually more interested in the plight of Igor, the young heir who Oleg controls.

episodes.title: The Key
episodes.plot: Norway's Kings and Jarls arrive at Harald's territory for the election of the King of all Norway, while King Olaf is confident of the result, the election may not run as smoothly as he thinks.

episodes.title: Death and the Serpent
episodes.plot: Bjorn is forced to act quickly in the aftermath of the election for the King of all Norway. The bandits attack Lagertha's village again, confident of victory. But when the defense boils down to single combat with Lagertha, victory for the bandits looks less certain. Back in Kattegat, haunted and paranoid, Hvitserk continues to unravel.

episodes.title: The Ice Maiden
episodes.plot: Bjorn returns to Kattegat; Harald gains a measure of revenge on Olaf; in Kiev, interesting news reaches Ivar and Igor about Prince Dir.

episodes.title: Valhalla Can Wait
episodes.plot: Bjorn faces a difficult decision. Ubbe and Torvi leave Kattegat, in search of new lands and perhaps old friends. Oleg's plans for the invasion of Scandinavia are taking shape, and King Harald is baffled by the origin of a mysterious raiding party.

episodes.title: Resurrection
episodes.plot: Ubbe and Torvi are able to meet their unknown wanderer while in Iceland; Bjorn reconsiders who his enemies truly are after Erik's scouting mission,which prompts him to convince an old nemesis to join him; Ivar reunites with a close figure.

episodes.title: The Best Laid Plans
episodes.plot: While Ivar and Igor continue to plot against Oleg, Kings Harald and Bjorn make frantic preparations to defend against the invasion,but the efforts of their quick work remain to be seen.

episodes.title: King of Kings
episodes.plot: In Iceland, Ubbe learns the truth about Kjetill and has a difficult decision to make. Back in Norway, the battle against the Rus has had grave consequences. But reinforcements have arrived, and Bjorn has an idea that may yet save the day.

episodes.title: All Change
episodes.plot: Ivar, Hvitserk, Prince Oleg and Prince Igor return to Kiev but the latter faces the consequences. With the leadership vacancy in Kattegat Erik, Gunnhild and Ingrid are making plans to fill it. Back to Kiev, Ivar and Prince Dir have new plans for Prince Oleg.

episodes.title: The Signal
episodes.plot: Trouble at sea heightens divisions near Iceland. A homecoming king with a new friend ends the spousal division threatened by an election in Kattegat. Good Friday is an opportunity for division among the Rus.

episodes.title: Lost Souls
episodes.plot: Prince Igor receives a hero's welcome in Novgorod but back in Kiev the mood is darker: prince Oleg will not be giving up the fight. Ubbe and the settlers find land but not the golden land.

episodes.title: All at Sea
episodes.plot: Fighting in Greenland means a change of destination and new dangers for Ubbe and company. A death in Kiev brings changes. Gunnhild makes her choice. Ivar gets a surprise and makes a decision.

episodes.title: The Final Straw
episodes.plot: Out in the open sea, Ubbe and the settlers are at the mercy of the elements. Meanwhile Ivar and Hvitserk return to Kattegat

episodes.title: The Raft of Medusa
episodes.plot: When king Alfred hears about the arrival of the sons of Ragnar, with an army he must take drastic action. So as the Vikings army makes camp & lies in wait, Alfred and his army abandon the royal villa and march to meet them.

episodes.title: It's Only Magic
episodes.plot: Ubbe and settlers find land but soon realize they are not alone. In Wessex, king Alfred has mustered up a large force to fight the Vikings. Meanwhile in Kattegat, Erik realizes that Ingrid had been using her powers on him

episodes.title: The Lord Giveth...
episodes.plot: In the new land, Ubbe and the settlers engage in careful diplomacy when they are surrounded by the locals. In Wessex the Vikings ambush the Saxon army, but Alfred is convinced the lord is with his army and refuses to retreat.

episodes.title: The Last Act
episodes.plot: The epic saga which began with Ragnar Lothbrok, the first Vikings leader to emerge from the mists of legend, comes to an end in a spectacular and shocking series finale which finds striking the new land and in England.

movies.title: Invasion
movies.plot: Earth is visited by an alien species that threatens humanity's existence. Events unfold in real time through the eyes of five ordinary people across the globe as they struggle to make sense of the chaos unraveling around them.

episodes.title: Something's Changed
episodes.plot: Mitsuki is taken to an alien ship in the Amazon jungle. Aneesha and her children take refuge with a group called the Movement.

episodes.title: Last Day
episodes.plot: Across the globe, strange and unexplainable events begin to unfold. A small-town sheriff senses something bigger is at play.

episodes.title: Crash
episodes.plot: Amid chaos, Aneesha makes a difficult decision for the sake of her family. Trevante, a Navy SEAL, investigates a distress call with his team.

episodes.title: Orion
episodes.plot: Mitsuki takes desperate measures, determined to uncover the truth. Caspar and Jamila discover just how dire their situation is.

episodes.title: The King Is Dead
episodes.plot: Trevante fears the worst until a locator beacon gives him hope. Mitsuki finds an ally in the most unexpected place.

episodes.title: Going Home
episodes.plot: The President of the United States gives an urgent global address in an attempt to prepare the world for what lies ahead.

episodes.title: Home Invasion
episodes.plot: In shock from the president's speech, Aneesha rushes back to her family only to find their safe haven--and their lives--threatened.

episodes.title: Hope
episodes.plot: Mitsuki commandeers a satellite station, hoping to make contact with outer space. Caspar reveals a strange secret he thinks is related to the invasion.

episodes.title: Contact
episodes.plot: Trevante's plane lands, but his journey home is just beginning. Caspar and Jamila brave London's streets, trying to make sense of his secret.

episodes.title: Full of Stars
episodes.plot: Mitsuki is determined to contact the Hoshi 12 before it's too late, as the military detains the Maliks and Caspar takes a risk that may kill him.

episodes.title: First Day
episodes.plot: The world, still reeling from global destruction, faces a new and unforeseen dawn.

movies.title: Yellowjackets
movies.plot: A wildly talented high school girls' soccer team become the unlucky survivors of a plane crash deep in the Canadian wilderness.

episodes.title: Friends, Romans, Countrymen
episodes.plot: Two months into winter the survivors cope with falling rations, low morale and their latest disastrous attempt to freeze a teammate out of the game. Taissa, Misty and Natalie all seek out best friends, both old and new.

episodes.title: Edible Complex
episodes.plot: Breaking off that friendship with the person who keeps ghosting you isn't always easy. Tai speeds through an unexpected reunion, Nat shacks up with Lottie, and Misty encounters a riddle wrapped in an enigma dressed in cargo shorts.

episodes.title: Digestif
episodes.plot: The girls experience an unusual hangover. Shauna learns the thrill of peer-to-peer car rentals. Natalie audits Lottie's class in emotional apiology. Misty hits the high seas - and the Yellowjackets throw a baby shower like no other.

episodes.title: Old Wounds
episodes.plot: Relive your youth by hitting the road! Go on vacation with a new friend! Hitchhike, if you must! Just make sure you pack a good playlist for the ride. Some recommendations from us: "Anything You Can Do" and "You Get What You Give".

episodes.title: Two Truths and a Lie
episodes.plot: Rise and shine and don't forget your booties because it's coooold out there. Misty makes a leap of faith, Natalie and Lottie play a game, Shauna finds herself unexpectedly randy, and Tai seeks out a movie recommendation.

episodes.title: Qui
episodes.plot: Trapped inside on a snow day, the Yellowjackets revisit the highlights, humiliations and traumas of Health Class. Tai and Van help each other rewind, while Misty explores joining a classic Cosmic American tribute band.

episodes.title: Burial
episodes.plot: Sometimes the best therapy is cranking the hits to 11, so today we're exploring the hardcore kid-care revival movement, 11 o'clock theatrical birdcore numbers, some late hits of the renovation-wave era (call us about a spin-off!), flower duets, and a classic live record. Out in the wilderness, Coach Scott does a great Karl Havoc impression for an unimpressed Misty.

episodes.title: It Chooses
episodes.plot: Shhh, it's only going to get worse from here. Despite the whole "winter never's gonna end" thing, the 1996 New Jersey state girls soccer champions decide to start their spring training early with an impromptu cardio session. Callie encounters an old flame, Van proves goalies never say die, most of the adults intentionally commune in the sharing shack, and, Lottie, baby, I hear the blues are calling for tossed salad and scrambled eggs. Mercy!

episodes.title: Storytelling
episodes.plot: Heavy is the head that wears the antler crown is a lesson you don't learn until much later in life... if you ever even learn it at all. Everything's about to get really wild(erness), and we're so excited (so excited!). Season finale.

movies.title: Seinfeld
movies.plot: The continuing misadventures of neurotic New York City stand-up comedian Jerry Seinfeld and his equally neurotic New York City friends.
filmingLocations: New York City, New York, USA

episodes.title: The Butter Shave
episodes.plot: Kramer discovers the amazing yet unknown uses of butter, but accidentally fries himself after using it as sunscreen.

episodes.title: The Voice
episodes.plot: George's colleagues try to force him to leave. Jerry makes fun of his girlfriend's bellybutton. Kramer hires an intern. Elaine gets back together with David Puddy.

episodes.title: The Serenity Now
episodes.plot: Jerry opens up his feelings. Elaine is getting hit on by the Jews. Kramer gets a screen door. George helps his father sell computers.

episodes.title: The Blood
episodes.plot: Jerry's parents hire their friend Izzy Mandelbaum to become Jerry's personal trainer while George decides to associate food and television with his love life.

episodes.title: The Junk Mail
episodes.plot: Kramer is annoyed with the catalogs he keeps getting in the mail. Elaine falls in love with a guy because of his smile. George's parents are avoiding him. Jerry can't find it in his heart to reject a gift from an old school friend.

episodes.title: The Merv Griffin Show
episodes.plot: George runs over a flock of pigeons. Jerry's girlfriend has a vintage toy collection she won't let him touch. A new co-worker is freaking Elaine out. Kramer rebuilds the set of "The Merv Griffin Show" in his apartment.

episodes.title: The Slicer
episodes.plot: Elaine borrows Kramer's meat slicer to feed her neighbor's cat while George tries to hide his not-so-great past from his new boss.

episodes.title: The Betrayal
episodes.plot: Elaine and the gang head to India to attend a wedding; Jerry betrays George by having sex with his prospective girlfriend; Kramer grapples with a malignant wish.

episodes.title: The Apology
episodes.plot: George is angered when an old acquaintance withholds a 12-Step-mandated apology; Jerry's girlfriend is too comfortable with her nudity; Elaine works with a germaphobe.

episodes.title: The Strike
episodes.plot: Jerry goes out with a woman who is beautiful one day and ugly the next. Kramer goes back to work at H&H Bagels. George makes up a charity. Elaine gives a fake number to a man.

episodes.title: The Dealership
episodes.plot: Jerry looks to buy a new car from Elaine's boyfriend. George tries to find a snack. Kramer test drives a car.

episodes.title: The Reverse Peephole
episodes.plot: Elaine is embarrassed by Puddy's fur coat. Kramer tries to keep Newman from getting evicted. George carries everything in his wallet. Jerry is through with wallets.

episodes.title: The Cartoon
episodes.plot: Sally Weaver makes fun of Jerry. George's new girlfriend looks just like Jerry. Kramer takes a vow of silence. Elaine gets a job drawing cartoons for the New Yorker.

episodes.title: The Strongbox
episodes.plot: George's new girlfriend refuses to break up with him. Jerry doesn't help out a neighbor. Elaine's new boyfriend is poor. Kramer tries to find a good place to hide his key for his strongbox.

episodes.title: The Wizard
episodes.plot: Jerry goes down to Florida for his father's birthday. George tries to avoid Susan's parents. Elaine can't figure out her new boyfriend's nationality. Kramer decides to retire.

episodes.title: The Burning
episodes.plot: Elaine finds out that Puddy is religious. Kramer pretends to have gonorrhea. Jerry's new girlfriend has a tractor story to tell him. George wants everyone at work to like him.

episodes.title: The Bookstore
episodes.plot: George is forced to buy a book he took with him into the bathroom. Jerry finds out that his Uncle Leo is a shoplifter. Elaine doesn't want to be known as the office skank. Kramer and Newman start a Hong Kong rickshaw business.

episodes.title: The Frogger
episodes.plot: George is obsessed with preserving his Frogger high score for posterity; Jerry stays one step ahead of a serial killer; Elaine eats Peterman's expensive cake:

episodes.title: The Maid
episodes.plot: Jerry gets into romance with his maid; George struggles to get the nickname "T-Bone" around the office; Elaine searches for a new telephone number.

episodes.title: The Puerto Rican Day
episodes.plot: Jerry, George, Kramer and Elaine get stuck in standstill traffic due to the massive Puerto Rican Day Parade.

episodes.title: The Chronicle
episodes.plot: Just as the four are about to go to the movies, Jerry looks back on the past nine years with the audience.

episodes.title: The Finale
episodes.plot: After George and Jerry land a production deal with NBC, the four head out for Paris on NBC's private plane and are waylaid in a small Massachusetts town.

episodes.title: The Foundation
episodes.plot: George enjoys the single life. Elaine takes over the catalog when J. Peterman suddenly goes missing. Kramer is taking karate lessons.

episodes.title: The Soul Mate
episodes.plot: George thinks the Board of Directors are talking behind his back. Kramer has a crush on Jerry's new girlfriend. Elaine doesn't see the big deal in having a baby.

episodes.title: The Bizarro Jerry
episodes.plot: George uses Susan's death to pick up women. Elaine's new friend is Jerry's exact opposite. Jerry's new girlfriend has manly hands. Kramer pretends to work for an upscale firm.

episodes.title: The Little Kicks
episodes.plot: Jerry is forced to bootleg a movie for Kramer's friend. George tries the "bad boy" image. No one has the heart to tell Elaine that she's a terrible dancer.

episodes.title: The Package
episodes.plot: A mysterious package arrives for Jerry. Elaine is curious about what the doctors are writing in her records. George tries to hit on the cute girl at the "One Hour Photo" place.

episodes.title: The Fatigues
episodes.plot: Jerry's new girlfriend's mentor is dating Bania. Kramer volunteers to host a Jewish singles mixer. George tries to study up on risk management. Elaine promotes a man she is afraid to fire.

episodes.title: The Checks
episodes.plot: Jerry gets hundreds of royalty checks, worth 12 cents each, for appearing on a Japanese TV program and gets writer's cramp. George and Jerry pitch their pilot to Japanese TV executives.

episodes.title: The Chicken Roaster
episodes.plot: Kenny Rogers' Roasters sets up shop across the street from Jerry and Kramer's apartments. Unfortunately, their unusually large chicken sign causes problems for everybody. Kramer and Jerry wind up switching apartments--and personalities--because of it. Jerry is freaked out by a wooden doll in Kramer's apartment, and Newman gets Kramer hooked on Kenny Roger's chicken. Elaine gets comfortable in her position as president of the catalog but is quickly accused of abusing the company credit card, especially when she buys George an expensive hat and George purposefully ...

episodes.title: The Abstinence
episodes.plot: Abstinence allows George to become a genius, but it turns Elaine into an idiot. Jerry gets bumped from career day at his old Jr. High School. Kramer turns his apartment into a smoking lounge and all the smoke disfigures his face.

episodes.title: The Andrea Doria
episodes.plot: A survivor of a shipwreck beats George out of an apartment, so George decides to tell the landlords the tragedies of his life in hopes of getting it back based on pity.

episodes.title: The Little Jerry
episodes.plot: Jerry bounces a check. Kramer buys a live chicken. George dates a female convict. Elaine dates a man who shaves his head.

episodes.title: The Money
episodes.plot: Jerry's parents believe he is financially unstable. Kramer has trouble sleeping with his girlfriend. Elaine enjoys her position as President of the J. Peterman catalog. George hopes to get his parents' money when they die.

episodes.title: The Comeback
episodes.plot: George tries to come up with a good comeback after someone insults him. Elaine falls in love with a mysterious employee at the video store. Kramer wants to die a certain way. Jerry takes advice from a tennis player who stinks.

episodes.title: The Van Buren Boys
episodes.plot: Kramer gets mixed up with a gang when he is mugged by them and mistakenly shows their secret sign.

episodes.title: The Susie
episodes.plot: Kramer sets his watch an hour ahead. George tries to avoid a breakup with his girlfriend. A colleague keeps calling Elaine, Susie. Jerry gambles on a basketball game, but the bookie can't pay him.

episodes.title: The Pothole
episodes.plot: Jerry accidentally knocks his girlfriend's toothbrush in the toilet. George drops his keys in a pothole that is paved over. A restaurant refuses to deliver food to Elaine's address. Kramer adopts a highway.

episodes.title: The English Patient
episodes.plot: Elaine is dragged to see the movie "The English Patient (1996) " on multiple occasions, even though she absolutely hates the film.

episodes.title: The Nap
episodes.plot: George takes a nap under his desk. Kramer swims in the East River. Jerry has some maintenance done on his kitchen. Elaine's new boyfriend buys her a new mattress.

episodes.title: The Yada Yada
episodes.plot: George's new girlfriend keeps including "Yada Yada" in her stories. Jerry is offended by Tim Whatley's Jewish jokes. Elaine tries to help her friends adopt a baby. Kramer and Mickey fight over two women.

episodes.title: The Millennium
episodes.plot: Kramer and Newman compete during the early planning of each of their millenium parties.

episodes.title: The Muffin Tops
episodes.plot: Elaine opens a new bakery that sells only the tops of the muffins.

episodes.title: The Summer of George
episodes.plot: Unemployed again, George decides to have a "memorable" summer. Jerry's new girlfriend has another dude. Kramer wins a Tony Award. A new woman at work is hostile towards Elaine.

movies.title: Moving
movies.plot: The quiet lives of three high school students with genetic superhuman abilities turn upside down when a mysterious organization starts to hunt them down one by one.

episodes.title: Senior Year
episodes.plot: Ordinary high school student Bongseok hides a secret.

episodes.title: Booyang: Family Support, Levitation
episodes.plot: Mihyun hides Bongseok's superpowers, but the mysterious incidents on social media make her anxious.
The closer Bongseok grows to Huisoo, the more risk of exposure he draws.

episodes.title: The Secret
episodes.plot: Bongseok's secret is exposed and Huisoo walks him home. Frank searches for his third target.

episodes.title: Recall
episodes.plot: Huisoo assures Bongseok that his secret is safe by revealing her own secret.

episodes.title: Bungaeman
episodes.plot: Jeon Gyedo's past is revealed. The NIS finds out information about Frank.

episodes.title: The Stranger
episodes.plot: Frank recalls his past as he eliminates his targets. After Frank's visit, Mihyun suppresses her son.

episodes.title: Black
episodes.plot: In 1994, Mihyun approaches black ops agent Kim Doosik at Min Yongjun's orders.

episodes.title: Humanists
episodes.plot: Doosik and Mihyun grow closer, and Doosik suggests that they deceive Min Yongjun.

episodes.title: The Monster
episodes.plot: A group of innocent teenagers with extraordinary abilities go head-to-head with some of the world's most powerful governments.

episodes.title: Romanticist
episodes.plot: Jihee gradually opens up to Juwon.

movies.title: The X Files
movies.plot: Two F.B.I. Agents, Fox Mulder the believer and Dana Scully the skeptic, investigate the strange and unexplained, while hidden forces work to impede their efforts.

episodes.title: My Struggle III
episodes.plot: Mulder and Scully learn that they aren't the only ones desperately searching for their long-lost son, William. The very fate of the world may depend on the outcome.

episodes.title: This
episodes.plot: A chilling secret is revealed when an old friend reaches out to Mulder and Scully in a seemingly impossible way.

episodes.title: Plus One
episodes.plot: Mulder and Scully investigate a case involving several deaths where the victims previously reported encountering their own doppelgangers. The clues lead to a pair of fraternal twins playing a dangerous game telepathically.

episodes.title: The Lost Art of Forehead Sweat
episodes.plot: Exploring the idea of The Mandela Effect, in which large groups of people remember an alternate history, Mulder and Scully find out how the X-Files themselves may really have originated.

episodes.title: Ghouli
episodes.plot: When a pair of teenage girls attack one another, each believing the other to be a monster, Mulder and Scully find that their investigation could possibly lead back to their long-lost son, William.

episodes.title: Kitten
episodes.plot: Skinner goes AWOL when his past comes back to haunt him. As Mulder and Scully try to track him down, their growing mistrust of him reaches its apex.

episodes.title: Rm9sbG93ZXJz
episodes.plot: In a world of ever-increasing automation and artificial intelligence, Mulder and Scully find themselves targets in a deadly game of cat and mouse.

episodes.title: Familiar
episodes.plot: Mulder and Scully suspect that darker forces are at play as they investigate a brutal animal attack on a little boy in Connecticut.

episodes.title: Nothing Lasts Forever
episodes.plot: While investigating human organ theft, Mulder and Scully uncover a mysterious cult consumed with macabre rituals.

episodes.title: My Struggle IV
episodes.plot: Mulder and Scully rush to find an on-the-run William while the Cigarette Smoking Man pushes forward with his ultimate plan.

episodes.title: My Struggle
episodes.plot: After the collapse of their relationship, former FBI agents Fox Mulder and Dana Scully are reunited by a TV host who promotes conspiracy theories about the government and believes that alien abductions are actually false flag operations.

episodes.title: Founder's Mutation
episodes.plot: A scientist working for the DOD commits suicide. Mulder and Scully start an investigation only to discover a secret mutation experiment.

episodes.title: Mulder & Scully Meet the Were-Monster
episodes.plot: Mulder questions his faith in the unexplained. He attempts to gather proof of the existence of the new creature he and Scully investigate before jumping to conclusions.

episodes.title: Home Again
episodes.plot: Scully receives bad news about her family while away on a case. Mulder finds a strange paint sample at the crime scene which leads him to the left-handed artist that created the main suspect. This brings back memories to Scully.

episodes.title: Babylon
episodes.plot: When a terrorist ends up in a coma, a pair of younger FBI agents ask Mulder and Scully for help communicating with the man, resembling them when their adventure first began and reminding them of just how far they have come.

episodes.title: My Struggle II
episodes.plot: Mulder and Scully uncover a shocking truth with global ramifications.

movies.title: Full Circle
movies.plot: An investigation into a botched kidnapping uncovers long-held secrets connecting multiple characters and cultures in present day New York City.
filmingLocations: New York City, New York, USA

episodes.title: Something Different
episodes.plot: To reverse her fate, Mrs. Mahabir hatches a plan to kidnap celebrity chef Jeff McCusker's grandson Jared.

episodes.title: Charger
episodes.plot: The McCuskers scramble to meet Aked's strangely specific demands, landing Derek in Washington Square Park. Amid personal and professional strife, Inspector Harmony stakes out the park as interweaving events come to a head.

episodes.title: Jared's Body
episodes.plot: While Natalia takes matters into her own hands, Sam visits her estranged uncle Gene after seeking advice from an old friend in law enforcement.

episodes.title: Safe in the Circle
episodes.plot: As Garmen weighs his options for his family, Derek finally confesses a long-held secret to Sam, and Inspector Harmony strikes a deal with Xavier.

episodes.title: Loyalty
episodes.plot: Faced with suspension, Inspector Harmony makes a last-ditch plea to Sam, while Gene and Jeff come face-to-face for the first time in years.

episodes.title: Essequibo
episodes.plot: As chaos breaks out at Mrs. Mahabir's ritual, Agent Harmony finds a definitive link between the McCuskers and Guyana.
